3
00:01:46.859 --> 00:01:48.235
It is time.

4
00:02:24.230 --> 00:02:25.689
It's beautiful. isn't it?

5
00:02:26.774 --> 00:02:28.359
I'm Ikaris.

6
00:02:29.360 --> 00:02:30.694
I'm Sersi.

7
00:05:46.348 --> 00:05:48.142
Thank you. Ajak.

8
00:07:32.621 --> 00:07:33.998
Shit.

9
00:07:37.543 --> 00:07:40.379
Excuse me. Excuse me.

10
00:07:59.106 --> 00:08:00.941
I know I'm late. Charlie.

11
00:08:06.155 --> 00:08:07.990
"In this broad Earth of ours.

12
00:08:08.157 --> 00:08:11.493
"Amid the measureless grossness
and the slag.

13
00:08:11.660 --> 00:08:14.872
"Enclosed and safe
within its central heart.

14
00:08:15.039 --> 00:08:17.625
"Nestles the seed Perfection."

15
00:08:18.459 --> 00:08:21.378
The poet's hope and optimism in humanity...

16
00:08:21.545 --> 00:08:26.008
echoes our recent universal victory.
the return of half our population...

17
00:08:26.175 --> 00:08:27.259
And. thank God. there she is.

18
00:08:28.761 --> 00:08:31.972
Our brilliant museum scientist. Ms. Sersi.
the person who will be...

19
00:08:32.139 --> 00:08:35.683
and was always supposed to be
giving you your presentation today.

20
00:08:35.893 --> 00:08:38.687
Thank you. Mr. Whitman.
Sorry I'm late. everyone.

21
00:08:38.854 --> 00:08:43.734
Today. we'll be learning about the importance
of apex predators in a balanced ecosystem.

22
00:08:45.069 --> 00:08:46.070
Poetry?

23
00:08:46.237 --> 00:08:49.782
I completely ran out of things to say.
and these kids make me nervous.

24
00:08:49.949 --> 00:08:52.159
Well. I thought you were
very charming. Professor.

25
00:08:52.743 --> 00:08:53.786
See you tonight.

26
00:08:53.953 --> 00:08:55.913
Ooh! "See you tonight."

27
00:08:56.664 --> 00:08:58.332
All right. settle down.

28
00:09:00.835 --> 00:09:01.836
So...

29
00:09:02.294 --> 00:09:04.713
who can tell me what an apex predator is?

30
00:09:05.172 --> 00:09:06.882
Animals that hunt their prey for food.

31
00:09:07.049 --> 00:09:08.217
Very good.

32
00:09:08.384 --> 00:09:12.054
Apex predators do hunt their prey for food.
like all predators.

33
00:09:12.221 --> 00:09:14.098
But one thing that sets them apart...

34
00:09:14.265 --> 00:09:18.894
is that there are no other animals
in their habitat strong enough to hunt them.

35
00:09:20.145 --> 00:09:21.480
Who can give me an example?

36
00:09:21.647 --> 00:09:22.648
Lions.

37
00:09:22.815 --> 00:09:24.567
-Wolves.
-Correct.

38
00:09:27.194 --> 00:09:28.404
Earthquake.

39
00:09:31.699 --> 00:09:32.825
Get down. Get down!

40
00:09:32.992 --> 00:09:35.828
It's an earthquake. everyone.
Get down! Under the tables!

41
00:09:36.996 --> 00:09:39.999
Let me help you.
Don't worry. it'll pass soon.

42
00:09:48.048 --> 00:09:49.967
It's all right. Come here.

43
00:09:51.886 --> 00:09:54.096
You're all right. You're all right.

44
00:10:37.223 --> 00:10:38.682
I like this song.

45
00:10:38.849 --> 00:10:39.975
Me. too.

46
00:10:41.018 --> 00:10:42.353
Do you wanna dance?

47
00:10:43.312 --> 00:10:44.480
Wait. what the hell?

48
00:10:45.439 --> 00:10:46.649
Your hand!

49
00:10:47.399 --> 00:10:51.237
You've had too much to drink.
I gotta go.

50
00:10:56.367 --> 00:11:00.788
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

51
00:11:00.955 --> 00:11:05.960
<i>Happy birthday. dear Dane</i>

52
00:11:06.126 --> 00:11:10.089
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

53
00:11:10.256 --> 00:11:12.216
-Hip. hip!
-Hooray!

54
00:11:19.098 --> 00:11:20.641
Is this from the Middle Ages?

55
00:11:20.808 --> 00:11:22.101
It has your family crest.

56
00:11:22.476 --> 00:11:24.728
It must have cost a fortune.

57
00:11:24.895 --> 00:11:26.522
I'm a good eBay bidder.

58
00:11:26.689 --> 00:11:27.690
Thank you.

59
00:11:28.357 --> 00:11:29.650
Happy birthday.

60
00:11:33.237 --> 00:11:37.908
So. have you given any more thought
to us moving in together?

61
00:11:38.075 --> 00:11:40.244
Yeah. I thought about it.

62
00:11:41.412 --> 00:11:43.414
I can't move in with you.

63
00:11:43.581 --> 00:11:45.416
Yeah. Thought you'd say that.

64
00:11:45.583 --> 00:11:46.417
I'm sorry.

65
00:11:46.584 --> 00:11:49.086
And I think I know why.

66
00:11:51.046 --> 00:11:52.464
Are you a wizard?

67
00:11:52.965 --> 00:11:53.966
What?

68
00:11:54.133 --> 00:11:55.926
Yeah. like Doctor Strange.

69
00:11:56.093 --> 00:11:57.094
No. I'm...

70
00:11:57.261 --> 00:11:59.555
I've noticed some unusual things
happen when I'm around you.

71
00:11:59.722 --> 00:12:02.808
Like our water always turns to coffee
whenever the waiter ignores us.

72
00:12:02.975 --> 00:12:03.976
That's your caffeine addiction talking.

73
00:12:04.143 --> 00:12:06.395
And Sprite says things...

74
00:12:07.021 --> 00:12:10.065
like you and your ex-boyfriend
broke up a century ago.

75
00:12:10.691 --> 00:12:11.692
She said that?

76
00:12:11.859 --> 00:12:13.068
And he can fly.

77
00:12:13.569 --> 00:12:15.154
He's a pilot.

78
00:12:16.030 --> 00:12:18.115
Get a room. you two.

79
00:12:18.282 --> 00:12:20.743
Can we go now?
It's past my bedtime.

80
00:12:24.872 --> 00:12:26.916
Are you really in love?

81
00:12:27.082 --> 00:12:28.334
What if I am?

82
00:12:28.501 --> 00:12:30.669
You better tell him the truth. then.

83
00:12:30.836 --> 00:12:32.463
I'm working on it.

84
00:12:43.974 --> 00:12:45.476
You guys wanna get pizza?

85
00:12:45.643 --> 00:12:46.894
No. thank you!

86
00:12:48.771 --> 00:12:52.233
He won't live forever. you know.
Move in with him.

87
00:12:52.858 --> 00:12:54.109
I live with you.

88
00:12:56.403 --> 00:12:57.530
Dane.

89
00:13:00.366 --> 00:13:02.117
Shit! Is that a Deviant?

90
00:13:02.284 --> 00:13:03.911
Dane. run!

91
00:13:15.381 --> 00:13:16.549
-Sersi?
-Let's go.

92
00:13:18.259 --> 00:13:20.636
-What is that thing?
-A Deviant!

93
00:13:20.803 --> 00:13:21.971
You said you killed them all!

94
00:13:22.137 --> 00:13:23.138
You told him that?

95
00:13:23.305 --> 00:13:24.932
-You believed me?
-I do now!

96
00:13:31.647 --> 00:13:33.190
What are you doing?

97
00:13:33.357 --> 00:13:34.400
Keep Dane safe!

98
00:13:34.567 --> 00:13:36.443
Sersi. wait! What?

99
00:13:44.910 --> 00:13:46.036
You're fine. dude.

100
00:13:46.203 --> 00:13:47.329
Sprite!

101
00:13:52.543 --> 00:13:54.461
No. Stairs.

102
00:14:31.498 --> 00:14:34.210
Run! Go! Go!

103
00:14:34.376 --> 00:14:35.753
-Go!
-Come on!

104
00:14:43.427 --> 00:14:44.803
It knows where we are!

105
00:14:45.221 --> 00:14:46.055
How?

106
00:14:46.222 --> 00:14:47.723
I don't know!

107
00:14:49.183 --> 00:14:50.184
Sprite!

108
00:14:56.148 --> 00:14:57.149
Sprite!

109
00:15:16.335 --> 00:15:17.419
Ikaris!

110
00:15:19.046 --> 00:15:20.506
Evening. ladies.

111
00:15:22.341 --> 00:15:23.425
Watch out!

112
00:15:39.650 --> 00:15:40.943
Wizard.

113
00:15:44.738 --> 00:15:45.823
Sorry.

114
00:16:07.052 --> 00:16:08.929
Did it just heal itself?

115
00:16:28.365 --> 00:16:29.575
Ikaris.

116
00:16:30.951 --> 00:16:33.245
It's good to see you.

117
00:16:33.704 --> 00:16:35.539
It's good to see you. too. Sprite.

118
00:16:41.754 --> 00:16:43.464
I'm Dane.

119
00:16:43.631 --> 00:16:45.049
Hello. Dane.

120
00:16:45.591 --> 00:16:47.760
Well. I guess you must be the pilot.

121
00:17:01.315 --> 00:17:04.484
We're Eternals. from a planet called Olympia.

122
00:17:05.152 --> 00:17:08.071
We came here 7.000 years ago on the <i>Domo...</i>

123
00:17:08.239 --> 00:17:11.659
our starship.
to protect humans from the Deviants.

124
00:17:12.617 --> 00:17:16.829
We thought we killed them all
five centuries ago. but now they're back.

125
00:17:19.290 --> 00:17:21.377
Look. if you don't want to move in with me.
you could just say.

126
00:17:21.544 --> 00:17:23.002
Dane. this is serious.

127
00:17:23.170 --> 00:17:26.173
I know. I'm just still getting over
the fact you're not a wizard.

128
00:17:26.715 --> 00:17:28.342
I was hoping you could change me
into a giraffe.

129
00:17:28.509 --> 00:17:30.010
I always wanted to be a giraffe
when I was a kid.

130
00:17:30.177 --> 00:17:32.471
It's too bad I can't change sentient beings.

131
00:17:32.638 --> 00:17:33.973
You would have made a very cute giraffe.

132
00:17:39.144 --> 00:17:41.188
Why didn't you guys help fight Thanos?

133
00:17:41.480 --> 00:17:44.567
Or any war? Or all the other terrible things
throughout history?

134
00:17:45.067 --> 00:17:47.319
We were instructed
not to interfere in any human conflicts...

135
00:17:47.486 --> 00:17:48.529
unless Deviants were involved.

136
00:17:48.696 --> 00:17:49.905
Why?

137
00:17:50.072 --> 00:17:55.244
If we'd protected humanity from everything
for 7.000 years...

138
00:17:55.411 --> 00:17:59.290
you'd never have had the chance to
develop in the way you were meant to.

139
00:17:59.456 --> 00:18:03.669
But if the Deviants were eradicated
a long time ago...

140
00:18:03.836 --> 00:18:05.171
why are you still here?

141
00:18:05.337 --> 00:18:06.422
We've been waiting...

142
00:18:06.881 --> 00:18:08.924
to be told we can go home.

143
00:18:10.759 --> 00:18:11.969
So...

144
00:18:12.803 --> 00:18:14.013
Ikaris.

145
00:18:14.847 --> 00:18:16.765
The boy who flew too close to the sun.

146
00:18:17.266 --> 00:18:19.602
Sprite made that story up
when we lived in Athens.

147
00:18:19.768 --> 00:18:22.062
In the fifth century BC?

148
00:18:22.229 --> 00:18:23.898
How long were you two together?

149
00:18:24.064 --> 00:18:25.566
5.000 years.

150
00:18:26.942 --> 00:18:28.944
I guess you can call that long-term.

151
00:18:30.112 --> 00:18:31.447
What happened?

152
00:18:31.822 --> 00:18:33.532
He left.

153
00:18:33.991 --> 00:18:37.286
I always thought he'd come back. but...

154
00:18:37.786 --> 00:18:39.538
he never did.

155
00:18:40.206 --> 00:18:41.498
So. I moved on.

156
00:18:41.957 --> 00:18:43.334
I'm glad you did.

157
00:18:44.376 --> 00:18:45.377
I'm sorry.

158
00:18:46.879 --> 00:18:48.297
I have to go.

159
00:18:57.515 --> 00:18:59.975
<i>This morning.
an unprecedented global earthquake...</i>

160
00:19:00.142 --> 00:19:01.727
<i>swept nation-states across the world...</i>

161
00:19:01.894 --> 00:19:03.938
<i>causing damage and panic.</i>

162
00:19:04.104 --> 00:19:06.690
<i>Many have speculated its connection
with the Blip.</i>

163
00:19:07.149 --> 00:19:09.109
<i>The UN has called for an emergency meeting...</i>

164
00:19:09.276 --> 00:19:11.403
That Deviant healed itself.

165
00:19:12.404 --> 00:19:14.448
They could never do that before.

166
00:19:16.200 --> 00:19:19.620
And it was coming after us instead of humans.
What's going on?

167
00:19:19.787 --> 00:19:22.498
I came to check on you
because of the earthquake.

168
00:19:22.665 --> 00:19:24.750
That Deviant is news to me.

169
00:19:27.753 --> 00:19:29.588
Something's happening to Earth.

170
00:19:30.881 --> 00:19:32.675
Can't be a coincidence.

171
00:19:34.176 --> 00:19:35.928
We need to find the others.

172
00:19:36.554 --> 00:19:38.514
I haven't seen some of them for centuries.

173
00:19:38.681 --> 00:19:40.599
I doubt much has changed.

174
00:19:50.818 --> 00:19:53.612
I'm sorry I hurt you. Sersi.

175
00:19:59.201 --> 00:20:01.120
But we need to stick together.

176
00:20:02.621 --> 00:20:04.582
And once I know you're safe.
I'll leave you alone.

177
00:20:05.791 --> 00:20:07.877
Let's go to Ajak first.

178
00:20:08.836 --> 00:20:10.754
She'll know what to do.

179
00:20:14.592 --> 00:20:16.302
You hear that. Sprite?

180
00:20:17.052 --> 00:20:18.971
Family reunion.

181
00:20:19.138 --> 00:20:20.848
It's about time.

182
00:20:32.943 --> 00:20:35.237
Hey. that one was mine!
Never mind.

183
00:22:10.457 --> 00:22:11.584
Ajak.

184
00:22:12.668 --> 00:22:13.752
Arishem.

185
00:22:14.628 --> 00:22:17.798
We continue to keep Babylon safe
from the Deviants.

186
00:22:17.965 --> 00:22:20.467
More people have come to seek refuge.

187
00:22:20.634 --> 00:22:23.387
It is now the largest city on Earth.

188
00:22:23.554 --> 00:22:26.390
The Eternals serving their missions
across the galaxies...

189
00:22:26.557 --> 00:22:28.267
will learn from your success.

190
00:22:28.684 --> 00:22:29.810
Thank you.

191
00:22:32.855 --> 00:22:36.066
I respect your grand design. Arishem.

192
00:22:37.151 --> 00:22:40.863
But I have noticed something special
about this planet.

193
00:22:42.990 --> 00:22:46.285
And I fear that maybe this time
the cost may...

194
00:22:46.452 --> 00:22:49.163
Do not become attached to this planet.

195
00:22:49.330 --> 00:22:53.167
You must focus on the true purpose
of your mission.

196
00:22:54.585 --> 00:22:56.086
I understand.

197
00:22:57.338 --> 00:22:59.173
I will not let you down.

198
00:23:23.864 --> 00:23:24.907
Phastos.

199
00:23:25.074 --> 00:23:27.993
Did you go to the party last night
like I told you to?

200
00:23:28.160 --> 00:23:29.161
The party. yeah.

201
00:23:29.328 --> 00:23:30.829
-Yeah. it was...
-He worked all night.

202
00:23:31.247 --> 00:23:32.248
Who was talking to you?

203
00:23:32.414 --> 00:23:34.583
Get a life.
And where is Sersi?

204
00:23:34.750 --> 00:23:35.751
Late as usual.

205
00:23:35.918 --> 00:23:38.921
I'm sorry. but I have something
very exciting to show you. okay?

206
00:23:39.964 --> 00:23:41.799
Wait till you see this.

207
00:23:45.594 --> 00:23:46.595
What is it?

208
00:23:46.762 --> 00:23:48.305
It's an engine.

209
00:23:48.472 --> 00:23:51.517
It moves steam from high pressure
to low pressure.

210
00:23:52.142 --> 00:23:54.728
It'll help them till their fields
at an incredibly fast rate.

211
00:23:55.104 --> 00:23:56.272
It's gonna freak them out.

212
00:23:56.689 --> 00:23:59.275
I mean. they only have
had the wheel 1.000 years. so...

213
00:24:00.526 --> 00:24:04.363
You know. we could do that thing
where you use your mind to control them...

214
00:24:04.530 --> 00:24:05.531
and then they could do it quicker.

215
00:24:05.698 --> 00:24:06.949
Ajak. you listening to this?

216
00:24:07.116 --> 00:24:09.952
Phastos. this steam...

217
00:24:10.119 --> 00:24:12.121
-Engine. It's a steam engine.
-It's too soon.

218
00:24:12.705 --> 00:24:13.706
And there she is.

219
00:24:14.123 --> 00:24:15.583
What did I miss?

220
00:24:15.833 --> 00:24:19.795
Nothing. Just the screams
of my deep disappointment.

221
00:24:19.962 --> 00:24:21.881
I am sure you have something simpler.

222
00:24:22.047 --> 00:24:22.882
Simple.

223
00:24:23.048 --> 00:24:24.633
Okay. let's see.

224
00:24:25.968 --> 00:24:28.929
Ladies and gentlemen. I present to you...

225
00:24:30.264 --> 00:24:31.599
the plow.

226
00:24:32.600 --> 00:24:34.560
'Cause that's what it does.

227
00:24:34.727 --> 00:24:36.020
Plows dirt.

228
00:24:36.187 --> 00:24:39.440
I met another group of settlers who are
building their homes in the northern fields.

229
00:24:39.607 --> 00:24:40.983
They'll need to plant their own crops.

230
00:24:41.525 --> 00:24:43.110
-Thanks. Sersi.
-Listen...

231
00:24:43.694 --> 00:24:47.156
humanity may be coming along
slower than some of us want.

232
00:24:48.115 --> 00:24:52.870
But there is no telling what wonders
they will discover as they advance.

233
00:25:23.025 --> 00:25:24.026
I just saw that.

234
00:25:24.193 --> 00:25:26.070
There's so many other chairs. man.

235
00:25:26.237 --> 00:25:27.404
You know. I could use my powers...

236
00:25:27.571 --> 00:25:29.156
Come and have a drink with me.

237
00:25:29.615 --> 00:25:30.616
No.

238
00:25:30.783 --> 00:25:32.535
I can't let you go
and fight Deviants on your own.

239
00:25:32.701 --> 00:25:34.870
-We need to guard the city.
-Get out of my way.

240
00:25:35.621 --> 00:25:38.499
I didn't come to this planet
to cower behind walls.

241
00:25:38.999 --> 00:25:42.419
We need to trust Arishem's design
for this planet.

242
00:25:44.880 --> 00:25:45.840
Thena.

243
00:25:48.133 --> 00:25:50.678
It's an honor to fight alongside you.

244
00:25:52.304 --> 00:25:53.556
And you.

245
00:25:57.101 --> 00:26:00.145
My beautiful Makkari. You're late.

246
00:26:55.075 --> 00:26:59.121
Well. she also says that
stealing is very. very bad.

247
00:27:06.212 --> 00:27:07.338
Deal.

248
00:27:18.849 --> 00:27:21.894
I promise I won't let my feelings for Sersi
distract me from my mission.

249
00:27:22.061 --> 00:27:25.231
Humans are far from being able to
protect themselves from the Deviants.

250
00:27:25.773 --> 00:27:27.316
We still have much to do.

251
00:27:28.984 --> 00:27:30.986
Your faith in Arishem is strong.

252
00:27:31.570 --> 00:27:33.072
I can feel it.

253
00:27:34.823 --> 00:27:37.284
But you are allowed to live a life. you know?

254
00:27:37.993 --> 00:27:40.329
Go tell Sersi how you feel.

255
00:28:06.522 --> 00:28:07.731
Try.

256
00:28:09.358 --> 00:28:11.360
Sorry. I'm making a mess.

257
00:28:14.572 --> 00:28:15.990
Well. not bad.

258
00:28:50.107 --> 00:28:51.275
It matches your eyes.

259
00:28:54.236 --> 00:28:56.155
You're learning their language now?

260
00:28:56.322 --> 00:28:58.449
If I want to spend more time with you...

261
00:28:58.616 --> 00:29:00.576
I need to get to know them.

262
00:29:06.957 --> 00:29:07.958
Wait. what did I say?

263
00:29:08.125 --> 00:29:11.337
You said. "I am very beautiful."

264
00:29:14.507 --> 00:29:15.549
You...

265
00:29:18.344 --> 00:29:21.055
You are very beautiful. Sersi.

266
00:29:32.983 --> 00:29:34.527
I'm yours. Sersi...

267
00:29:35.694 --> 00:29:36.695
if you'll have me.

268
00:30:21.657 --> 00:30:23.242
I love you. Ikaris.

269
00:30:26.036 --> 00:30:27.663
I love you. Sersi.

270
00:31:35.105 --> 00:31:36.398
Hello?

271
00:31:40.069 --> 00:31:41.237
Ajak?

272
00:32:06.011 --> 00:32:07.638
Ajak!

273
00:32:33.581 --> 00:32:35.249
It was a Deviant.

274
00:32:42.673 --> 00:32:45.092
<i>Our love</i>

275
00:32:45.259 --> 00:32:48.596
<i>And our devotion</i>

276
00:32:49.263 --> 00:32:54.268
<i>Were as deep as any ocean</i>

277
00:32:59.190 --> 00:33:01.275
It was the last time I saw her.

278
00:33:03.152 --> 00:33:07.323
Ajak asked me to check on Sersi.
so I went to London.

279
00:33:09.533 --> 00:33:12.953
Turned out. both of us were lonely
and we needed each other.

280
00:33:14.747 --> 00:33:16.790
I guess. in her way...

281
00:33:16.957 --> 00:33:19.960
Ajak never stopped trying to take care of us.

282
00:33:28.511 --> 00:33:29.887
Bye. Ajak.

283
00:33:34.475 --> 00:33:36.977
It's the first time in 7.000 years
one of us has died.

284
00:33:37.520 --> 00:33:40.064
I think the Deviant
that attacked us in London...

285
00:33:40.231 --> 00:33:42.024
killed Ajak and absorbed her power.

286
00:33:42.191 --> 00:33:43.901
Deviants have never done that in the past.

287
00:33:44.068 --> 00:33:46.111
It healed itself just like Ajak.

288
00:33:46.612 --> 00:33:49.198
I swear. I almost heard it speak.

289
00:34:16.225 --> 00:34:17.059
Arishem.

290
00:34:17.226 --> 00:34:18.185
Sersi.

291
00:34:18.351 --> 00:34:19.978
It is almost time.

292
00:34:21.856 --> 00:34:24.065
Sersi! Sersi! Are you okay?

293
00:34:24.650 --> 00:34:26.110
What happened. Sersi?

294
00:34:29.321 --> 00:34:31.739
The sphere
that Ajak used to talk with Arishem...

295
00:34:31.907 --> 00:34:34.409
it came out of her body and went inside me.

296
00:34:34.577 --> 00:34:36.286
Did you talk with Arishem?

297
00:34:36.911 --> 00:34:38.539
Yes. He said...

298
00:34:39.123 --> 00:34:40.875
it's almost time.

299
00:34:42.126 --> 00:34:43.835
Can you try talking to him again?

300
00:34:44.795 --> 00:34:46.213
I don't know how.

301
00:34:46.380 --> 00:34:48.257
But she chose you to replace her.

302
00:34:48.924 --> 00:34:50.176
And she gave you the sphere.

303
00:34:50.342 --> 00:34:51.427
Hold on. Sprite.

304
00:34:53.137 --> 00:34:54.554
Are you sure you talked with Arishem?

305
00:34:54.722 --> 00:34:56.015
What else would it be?

306
00:34:57.266 --> 00:34:58.517
Mahd Wy'ry.

307
00:35:34.803 --> 00:35:36.055
Where are the others?

308
00:35:39.850 --> 00:35:41.477
There were more Deviants than you said.

309
00:35:41.644 --> 00:35:43.312
Well. I'm sure that was a lot of fun for you.

310
00:35:43.646 --> 00:35:44.855
It was.

311
00:35:47.024 --> 00:35:49.109
Once the others kill these last Deviants...

312
00:35:49.860 --> 00:35:52.112
we will have eliminated them all
from the planet.

313
00:36:10.214 --> 00:36:11.549
Don't.

314
00:36:12.883 --> 00:36:15.344
We don't interfere in their wars.

315
00:36:16.470 --> 00:36:18.013
This isn't war.

316
00:36:18.180 --> 00:36:19.974
It's genocide.

317
00:36:20.349 --> 00:36:22.393
Their weapons have become too deadly.

318
00:36:23.769 --> 00:36:26.939
Maybe it wasn't such a good idea
helping them advance. Phastos.

319
00:36:27.147 --> 00:36:30.693
Technology is a part of
their evolutionary process. Druig.

320
00:36:30.860 --> 00:36:32.403
It's not exactly something that I can stop.

321
00:36:32.570 --> 00:36:34.572
No. you can't. But I can.

322
00:36:36.657 --> 00:36:38.325
It's too late.

323
00:36:38.492 --> 00:36:40.953
-Thena?
-Everyone is going to die.

324
00:36:42.079 --> 00:36:43.080
Are you okay?

325
00:36:44.498 --> 00:36:45.499
Thena?

326
00:36:48.752 --> 00:36:50.588
-Thena? Thena. no!
-Thena!

327
00:37:19.783 --> 00:37:22.119
Don't listen to your head. Thena.

328
00:37:23.120 --> 00:37:25.080
Listen to my voice.

329
00:37:26.790 --> 00:37:28.459
You are safe.

330
00:37:29.585 --> 00:37:32.171
You are loved.

331
00:37:33.088 --> 00:37:34.882
You're our Thena.

332
00:37:42.181 --> 00:37:43.349
Hey. Thena!

333
00:37:43.516 --> 00:37:45.768
Hey! Stop. stop. stop!

334
00:38:04.078 --> 00:38:05.663
-Is she okay?
-Yeah.

335
00:38:06.956 --> 00:38:08.082
Sersi.

336
00:38:08.249 --> 00:38:09.250
Thena. please.

337
00:38:09.875 --> 00:38:11.335
Come back to us.

338
00:38:12.002 --> 00:38:13.045
Okay.

339
00:38:29.603 --> 00:38:31.730
I thought Mahd Wy'ry was a myth.

340
00:38:35.150 --> 00:38:36.819
There is no cure...

341
00:38:37.695 --> 00:38:39.154
so no one really talks about it.

342
00:38:43.993 --> 00:38:44.994
What happened?

343
00:38:45.160 --> 00:38:46.245
Thena.

344
00:38:46.412 --> 00:38:47.955
You attacked everyone.

345
00:38:48.372 --> 00:38:50.749
Wounded Sersi. Phastos...

346
00:38:50.916 --> 00:38:52.877
you nearly killed Makkari.

347
00:38:55.337 --> 00:38:57.173
I don't remember.

348
00:38:57.339 --> 00:38:59.425
You have Mahd Wy'ry.

349
00:38:59.592 --> 00:39:03.762
Your mind is fracturing
under the weight of your memories.

350
00:39:03.929 --> 00:39:08.184
And all I can do is erase them
so that you can start over.

351
00:39:09.310 --> 00:39:12.563
I will have to inform Arishem
and take you back to the ship...

352
00:39:12.730 --> 00:39:15.566
where we have the technology to help you.

353
00:39:18.152 --> 00:39:20.112
What if it happens again?
She could've killed you.

354
00:39:20.279 --> 00:39:21.780
She could have killed all of us.

355
00:39:21.947 --> 00:39:22.948
Please.

356
00:39:24.617 --> 00:39:27.119
Please. I want to remember.

357
00:39:28.162 --> 00:39:30.039
I want to remember my life.

358
00:39:30.664 --> 00:39:32.166
Thena. I love you.

359
00:39:32.333 --> 00:39:33.959
But listen to me.

360
00:39:34.126 --> 00:39:37.713
It's not important if you remember or not.

361
00:39:38.255 --> 00:39:40.007
Your spirit will remain.

362
00:39:40.174 --> 00:39:42.968
You will always be Thena deep inside.

363
00:39:43.427 --> 00:39:44.428
Trust me.

364
00:39:44.595 --> 00:39:45.846
Why should she trust you?

365
00:39:47.640 --> 00:39:50.267
You're asking her
to let you erase who she is.

366
00:39:50.434 --> 00:39:52.269
Druig. I know you're upset. but...

367
00:39:52.436 --> 00:39:53.479
Upset?

368
00:39:55.481 --> 00:39:58.692
We've trusted you for 7.000 years.
and look where you've gotten us.

369
00:40:00.194 --> 00:40:05.199
I've watched humans destroy each other
when I could stop it all in a heartbeat.

370
00:40:06.992 --> 00:40:09.745
Do you know what that does to someone
after centuries?

371
00:40:11.038 --> 00:40:13.123
Could our mission have been a mistake?

372
00:40:13.916 --> 00:40:17.127
Are we really helping these people
build a better world. huh?

373
00:40:26.178 --> 00:40:28.556
We're just like the soldiers down there.

374
00:40:29.390 --> 00:40:31.559
Pawns to their leaders.

375
00:40:32.226 --> 00:40:34.311
Blinded by loyalty.

376
00:40:37.356 --> 00:40:39.066
It ends now.

377
00:40:56.834 --> 00:40:57.835
Let them go.

378
00:40:58.002 --> 00:40:59.336
You're gonna have to make me.

379
00:40:59.503 --> 00:41:00.504
Stop.

380
00:41:07.052 --> 00:41:08.596
If you wanna stop me...

381
00:41:09.889 --> 00:41:11.765
you're gonna have to kill me.

382
00:41:35.497 --> 00:41:37.333
I'll watch over Thena.

383
00:41:38.042 --> 00:41:39.126
Let her keep her memories.

384
00:41:40.377 --> 00:41:42.421
One day. when she attacks you...

385
00:41:43.047 --> 00:41:45.090
you might have to kill her.

386
00:41:51.222 --> 00:41:52.973
We'll take that chance.

387
00:42:02.775 --> 00:42:03.943
You may all go.

388
00:42:06.403 --> 00:42:08.113
The Deviants are gone.

389
00:42:08.989 --> 00:42:11.951
There is no reason
for you to stay with me.

390
00:42:12.117 --> 00:42:13.702
Shouldn't you ask Arishem first?

391
00:42:13.869 --> 00:42:15.704
We're a team. we should stay together.

392
00:42:15.871 --> 00:42:18.791
I didn't ask you for your advice. Ikaris.

393
00:42:18.958 --> 00:42:21.293
Do not forget your place.

394
00:42:24.505 --> 00:42:26.757
This is where we say goodbye.

395
00:42:27.883 --> 00:42:29.468
You are free to go.

396
00:42:30.845 --> 00:42:33.013
I want you to go out there.

397
00:42:33.180 --> 00:42:35.933
And live a life for yourselves.

398
00:42:36.100 --> 00:42:37.852
Not as soldiers.

399
00:42:38.561 --> 00:42:41.522
Not with the purpose
you were given.

400
00:42:41.897 --> 00:42:44.692
Find your own purpose.

401
00:42:45.568 --> 00:42:49.738
And one day. when we see each other again...

402
00:42:52.199 --> 00:42:55.202
I want you to tell me what you found.

403
00:42:59.582 --> 00:43:01.500
<i>Come my way</i>

404
00:43:02.918 --> 00:43:05.171
{\an8}<i>Get the evil away</i>

405
00:43:06.547 --> 00:43:08.757
<i>You came to save</i>

406
00:43:10.259 --> 00:43:12.511
<i>And now you're here</i>

407
00:43:15.973 --> 00:43:19.435
<i>Now you have come home
Give it all to me</i>

408
00:43:19.602 --> 00:43:23.314
<i>You would risk it all
For my victory</i>

409
00:43:23.480 --> 00:43:27.401
<i>Waiting for you
Scarcely can I</i>

410
00:44:05.147 --> 00:44:07.441
I am Karun Patel.

411
00:44:08.067 --> 00:44:09.318
Kingo's valet.

412
00:44:10.152 --> 00:44:13.531
It's truly an honor to be in the presence
of the great Eternals.

413
00:44:15.324 --> 00:44:18.786
<i>The ring of fire
Like the sun</i>

414
00:44:18.953 --> 00:44:22.623
<i>You have risen
Mighty one</i>

415
00:44:31.674 --> 00:44:34.802
Cut! Okay. everyone. that was good.

416
00:44:34.969 --> 00:44:36.720
But we could do 10% better.

417
00:44:36.887 --> 00:44:38.973
That was beautiful. Very. very good.

418
00:44:39.139 --> 00:44:40.140
Really. so good.

419
00:44:41.225 --> 00:44:43.310
My friends from college are here.

420
00:44:44.019 --> 00:44:44.854
Hello. boss!

421
00:44:45.563 --> 00:44:48.148
Perfect timing! Welcome to the set of...

422
00:44:51.277 --> 00:44:52.361
I'm playing you!

423
00:44:52.528 --> 00:44:54.196
-You like the costume?
-We need to talk.

424
00:44:54.363 --> 00:44:55.698
Tell the director
I have some notes for him...

425
00:44:55.865 --> 00:44:57.032
We need to talk to you in private.

426
00:44:57.658 --> 00:45:01.120
Oh. Karun. he's worked with me for 50 years.
I trust him completely.

427
00:45:01.287 --> 00:45:03.706
Actually. when we first met.
he thought I was a vampire...

428
00:45:03.873 --> 00:45:05.165
and he tried to stake me through the heart.

429
00:45:05.708 --> 00:45:07.418
I have apologized so many times.

430
00:45:07.585 --> 00:45:10.171
Not quite enough times. Very close. though.
I'll let you know.

431
00:45:10.337 --> 00:45:13.340
I have to get ready for the next scene.
Come to my tent. we'll talk there.

432
00:45:13.507 --> 00:45:14.675
You guys are gonna love the next scene.

433
00:45:14.842 --> 00:45:17.761
I come in on a wire
'cause. you know. I can't fly.

434
00:45:17.928 --> 00:45:19.680
Wait. are we getting back together?

435
00:45:19.847 --> 00:45:20.848
We need to talk.

436
00:45:21.015 --> 00:45:21.974
I've been waiting for the day...

437
00:45:22.141 --> 00:45:24.310
the world learns the true identity
of the Shadow Warrior.

438
00:45:24.476 --> 00:45:25.936
Ajak's dead.

439
00:45:31.025 --> 00:45:32.401
She was killed.

440
00:45:33.319 --> 00:45:34.695
It was a Deviant.

441
00:45:39.241 --> 00:45:40.868
The Deviants are back.

442
00:45:41.035 --> 00:45:42.494
We don't know how many there are.

443
00:45:46.415 --> 00:45:47.833
You need to come with us.

444
00:46:04.058 --> 00:46:06.185
I can't just go. I mean.
all these people depend on me.

445
00:46:06.352 --> 00:46:08.896
We just started shooting this movie.
It's the first of a trilogy.

446
00:46:09.522 --> 00:46:11.524
We just got BTS to do a cameo...

447
00:46:13.108 --> 00:46:14.276
Sir...

448
00:46:14.693 --> 00:46:16.654
-may I say something?
-Please don't say anything.

449
00:46:16.820 --> 00:46:17.863
I think you should go.

450
00:46:18.030 --> 00:46:19.240
I just said don't say anything.

451
00:46:19.406 --> 00:46:23.661
"Life affords no greater duty
than to protect one's family!"

452
00:46:24.537 --> 00:46:26.497
Remember? It's your favorite line...

453
00:46:26.664 --> 00:46:31.168
from <i>The Shadow Warrior 2: Voyage of Time.</i>

454
00:46:31.919 --> 00:46:33.754
Your family needs you.

455
00:46:44.682 --> 00:46:46.851
Seven thousand years.

456
00:46:48.644 --> 00:46:52.356
That's how long the battle between Eternals
and Deviants has raged for.

457
00:46:52.982 --> 00:46:54.984
You think I'm a movie star.

458
00:46:55.150 --> 00:46:57.987
<i>Well. I am. But I am also...</i>

459
00:46:58.904 --> 00:47:00.489
<i>an Eternal.</i>

460
00:47:00.656 --> 00:47:02.157
<i>Kingo. what are you doing?</i>

461
00:47:03.033 --> 00:47:06.287
I think we should be remembered. so...

462
00:47:06.453 --> 00:47:10.499
I am making a documentary about us.

463
00:47:10.666 --> 00:47:13.669
You are about to meet
my fellow Eternal. Sprite.

464
00:47:13.836 --> 00:47:16.046
Sprite. tell them about yourself.

465
00:47:16.213 --> 00:47:17.548
Oh. wait.

466
00:47:21.427 --> 00:47:23.929
<i>Okay. well. we'll circle back to her.</i>

467
00:47:24.597 --> 00:47:26.807
This is Sersi.

468
00:47:27.391 --> 00:47:28.392
Sersi...

469
00:47:28.559 --> 00:47:30.394
tell them about yourself.

470
00:47:32.646 --> 00:47:33.647
<i>We're rolling.</i>

471
00:47:33.814 --> 00:47:34.648
<i>Well...</i>

472
00:47:36.317 --> 00:47:40.905
I can change a rock into water.

473
00:47:41.697 --> 00:47:44.200
I could turn a rock into wood.

474
00:47:44.366 --> 00:47:46.452
Or a rock into metal.

475
00:47:46.619 --> 00:47:48.787
Actually. one time. I turned a rock into air.

476
00:47:48.954 --> 00:47:49.830
Cut.

477
00:47:50.414 --> 00:47:54.043
You know what? Why don't you think about it.
and we'll get back to you. okay?

478
00:47:54.210 --> 00:47:55.461
Let's go.

479
00:47:58.172 --> 00:48:00.508
Sprite says you're addicted to this thing.

480
00:48:02.635 --> 00:48:03.802
Oh. this?

481
00:48:04.678 --> 00:48:06.180
Look at this.

482
00:48:09.016 --> 00:48:11.143
You know. seeing as we don't age.

483
00:48:11.644 --> 00:48:13.479
I think you look quite good.

484
00:48:15.064 --> 00:48:16.065
Don't you?

485
00:48:20.236 --> 00:48:24.114
Nobody ever wonders how you managed to be
the leading man for over 100 years?

486
00:48:24.281 --> 00:48:25.824
I don't know what you're talking about.

487
00:48:25.991 --> 00:48:28.160
That is my great-great-grandfather...

488
00:48:28.327 --> 00:48:30.663
that is my great-grandfather...

489
00:48:30.829 --> 00:48:31.830
grandfather...

490
00:48:31.997 --> 00:48:34.041
father. and me.

491
00:48:34.208 --> 00:48:37.211
I'm part of the greatest dynasty
in the history of Bollywood.

492
00:48:37.670 --> 00:48:38.671
Pretty impressive. right?

493
00:48:38.838 --> 00:48:40.881
You abandoned me in Macedonia.

494
00:48:42.633 --> 00:48:46.095
Okay. I got sick of moving every five years.

495
00:48:46.262 --> 00:48:49.223
People freak out
when they notice that you don't...

496
00:48:51.308 --> 00:48:52.309
age.

497
00:48:53.561 --> 00:48:55.020
I thought we were friends.

498
00:49:02.027 --> 00:49:03.904
Do you know why I love movies?

499
00:49:04.780 --> 00:49:06.365
Because of you.

500
00:49:06.532 --> 00:49:09.326
I missed sitting in the audience.
listening to your stories...

501
00:49:09.493 --> 00:49:10.744
watching your illusions.

502
00:49:15.583 --> 00:49:17.793
We should've all stayed together.

503
00:49:19.795 --> 00:49:21.881
Ajak would still be alive.

504
00:49:23.465 --> 00:49:25.259
She should have never let us go.

505
00:49:36.103 --> 00:49:37.897
This is the Deviant you fought in London?

506
00:49:38.314 --> 00:49:39.732
It's different.

507
00:49:40.524 --> 00:49:42.568
There must be more out there than we thought.

508
00:49:44.153 --> 00:49:46.155
Is this a Deviant. sir?

509
00:49:46.322 --> 00:49:47.364
Yep.

510
00:49:48.282 --> 00:49:49.992
It's a beautiful creature.

511
00:49:50.159 --> 00:49:53.621
What? This? This?
No. It's hideous.

512
00:49:53.787 --> 00:49:56.415
You've never had one
try to bite your head off. Roll.

513
00:49:58.000 --> 00:50:01.295
You're about to meet two of the
greatest warriors the world has ever known.

514
00:50:01.754 --> 00:50:05.174
<i>Thena. legendary. deadly. fashionable.</i>

515
00:50:05.341 --> 00:50:07.051
And her trusty friend...

516
00:50:07.218 --> 00:50:08.302
Door.

517
00:50:09.011 --> 00:50:10.930
...a mighty powerhouse of strength...

518
00:50:11.096 --> 00:50:14.058
<i>the fearsome Gilgamesh!</i>

519
00:50:16.560 --> 00:50:17.603
Gilgamesh!

520
00:50:20.606 --> 00:50:22.191
<i>What took you so long?</i>

521
00:50:25.319 --> 00:50:27.112
You look younger today. Sprite.

522
00:50:27.279 --> 00:50:28.781
I have the same apron.

523
00:50:29.281 --> 00:50:30.574
Who the hell are you?

524
00:50:30.991 --> 00:50:33.077
I'm Karun. Kingo's valet.

525
00:50:33.702 --> 00:50:36.330
Oh. valet. Like Alfred in <i>Batman.</i>

526
00:50:36.789 --> 00:50:39.166
Gilgamesh. The Deviants are back.

527
00:50:39.333 --> 00:50:41.919
No shit. I could have used some help.

528
00:50:42.086 --> 00:50:44.547
We were attacked by a Deviant in London. too.

529
00:50:44.713 --> 00:50:46.465
Even Ikaris couldn't kill it.

530
00:50:47.341 --> 00:50:48.342
You couldn't?

531
00:50:48.509 --> 00:50:50.511
I was distracted.

532
00:50:50.678 --> 00:50:51.971
Sure. man.

533
00:50:52.888 --> 00:50:55.474
Hey. you guys wanna try my pie?

534
00:50:57.768 --> 00:50:59.353
I'm sorry. Gil.

535
00:51:00.020 --> 00:51:01.397
Ajak's dead.

536
00:51:04.233 --> 00:51:05.526
It's true. buddy.

537
00:51:06.068 --> 00:51:07.403
We lost her.

538
00:51:39.393 --> 00:51:40.561
Sersi.

539
00:51:41.979 --> 00:51:43.856
The attack triggered her.

540
00:51:44.023 --> 00:51:45.941
She's no fun to be around right now.

541
00:51:47.526 --> 00:51:49.028
Hey. Thena.

542
00:51:49.445 --> 00:51:51.322
Look who's here.

543
00:51:52.198 --> 00:51:53.365
Give me your hand.

544
00:51:56.118 --> 00:51:57.161
Thena.

545
00:51:57.578 --> 00:52:00.331
Everyone in Centuri-6 is going to die.

546
00:52:01.040 --> 00:52:02.082
Give me your hand.

547
00:52:02.249 --> 00:52:04.460
It's too late. We can't save them.

548
00:52:04.627 --> 00:52:05.503
Thena.

549
00:52:12.551 --> 00:52:13.802
Thena.

550
00:52:14.512 --> 00:52:17.223
We came to Earth together on our ship.

551
00:52:19.517 --> 00:52:21.227
You're an Eternal.

552
00:52:22.061 --> 00:52:24.813
The greatest warrior of Olympia.

553
00:52:24.980 --> 00:52:27.066
The legendary protector of Athens.

554
00:52:28.567 --> 00:52:30.486
The goddess of war.

555
00:52:32.488 --> 00:52:34.823
Remember who you are.

556
00:52:42.873 --> 00:52:44.333
Remember.

557
00:53:00.224 --> 00:53:02.184
-Thena.
-Hi.

558
00:53:03.143 --> 00:53:04.144
Hello.

559
00:53:04.520 --> 00:53:06.480
Hey. who's your gardener?

560
00:53:07.982 --> 00:53:10.192
This is just what you guys eat every day?

561
00:53:10.359 --> 00:53:11.944
-Yeah. this is amazing.
-Every day.

562
00:53:12.111 --> 00:53:14.196
-Thank you for this.
-Oh. you're welcome.

563
00:53:14.363 --> 00:53:15.531
Help yourself.

564
00:53:15.698 --> 00:53:18.868
This one is a trio of wine. beer. and mead.

565
00:53:19.034 --> 00:53:21.495
Made for all the soldiers
in the battle of Troy.

566
00:53:22.162 --> 00:53:23.747
That's so thoughtful.

567
00:53:30.546 --> 00:53:32.131
Should she be drinking?

568
00:53:33.382 --> 00:53:36.802
No. hers is non-alcoholic. For kids.

569
00:53:38.888 --> 00:53:41.056
I gave you the same thing. Sprite.

570
00:53:43.684 --> 00:53:44.685
For kids.

571
00:53:46.937 --> 00:53:48.230
I was just kidding.

572
00:53:48.397 --> 00:53:51.775
Yours is a secret brew
Odin taught me as a thank-you...

573
00:53:51.942 --> 00:53:55.070
after we helped defeat Laufey's army
in Tonsberg.

574
00:53:55.237 --> 00:53:56.322
What?

575
00:53:57.656 --> 00:53:58.657
I'm a big baby.

576
00:53:58.824 --> 00:54:00.701
Very mature. Can you stop?

577
00:54:01.577 --> 00:54:02.912
-Stop.
-Speaking of Odin...

578
00:54:03.078 --> 00:54:05.664
Thor used to follow me around
when he was a little kid.

579
00:54:05.831 --> 00:54:08.459
Now he's a famous Avenger
and won't return my calls.

580
00:54:08.626 --> 00:54:10.961
So. now that Captain Rogers
and Iron Man are both gone...

581
00:54:11.128 --> 00:54:13.088
who do you think is gonna lead the Avengers?

582
00:54:13.756 --> 00:54:15.257
I could lead them.

583
00:54:15.424 --> 00:54:16.634
I figure I'd be good at that.

584
00:54:16.800 --> 00:54:17.635
Yeah. you would.

585
00:54:17.968 --> 00:54:20.012
Ajak didn't even choose you to lead us.

586
00:54:20.763 --> 00:54:22.598
Ouch. Gil. Ouch.

587
00:54:22.765 --> 00:54:23.766
-Harsh.
-I'm gonna let that one slide...

588
00:54:23.933 --> 00:54:26.477
because. you know. you've always been bitter
that I can fly and you can't.

589
00:54:26.644 --> 00:54:27.853
So what. you can fly.

590
00:54:28.020 --> 00:54:29.730
I'm better-looking. everybody knows that.

591
00:54:29.897 --> 00:54:30.898
Where you going?

592
00:54:32.900 --> 00:54:34.568
I'm just gonna get some air.

593
00:54:40.449 --> 00:54:41.825
This is really good. Gil.

594
00:54:41.992 --> 00:54:45.204
You know. I could sell this.
Put my face on it. move some units.

595
00:54:45.371 --> 00:54:46.664
I made it from corn.

596
00:54:46.830 --> 00:54:50.668
I chew each kernel myself
and ferment it in my spit.

597
00:55:04.723 --> 00:55:07.560
Is this the Centuri-6
Thena was talking about?

598
00:55:07.893 --> 00:55:09.687
Yeah. it's a planet.

599
00:55:10.604 --> 00:55:14.233
She thinks she used to live there
until it was destroyed.

600
00:55:14.400 --> 00:55:18.070
Always talks about
massive quakes ripping it apart.

601
00:55:18.237 --> 00:55:20.155
Everyone died. including herself.

602
00:55:20.573 --> 00:55:23.242
We had an unprecedented global earthquake
three days ago.

603
00:55:23.909 --> 00:55:25.744
Oh. that's what that was.

604
00:55:25.911 --> 00:55:27.663
I thought I was drunk.

605
00:55:28.372 --> 00:55:30.583
Ajak chose me to lead us. but...

606
00:55:31.333 --> 00:55:33.878
I can't even figure out
how to speak to Arishem.

607
00:55:34.044 --> 00:55:35.921
I've tried so many times.

608
00:55:37.131 --> 00:55:39.216
Maybe you're trying too hard.

609
00:55:40.176 --> 00:55:42.761
Sometimes. you just have to listen.

610
00:56:30.226 --> 00:56:31.352
Sersi.

611
00:56:32.228 --> 00:56:33.312
Arishem.

612
00:56:33.896 --> 00:56:35.773
Ajak was killed by a Deviant.

613
00:56:35.940 --> 00:56:38.359
We think it absorbed her power.

614
00:56:38.526 --> 00:56:41.278
And something unusual is happening to Earth.

615
00:56:41.445 --> 00:56:44.448
It is a side effect of the emergence.

616
00:56:45.866 --> 00:56:47.493
The emergence?

617
00:56:48.244 --> 00:56:52.414
It is time for you to learn
the true purpose of your mission.

618
00:56:52.581 --> 00:56:57.920
You were sent to Earth to
bring forth the Celestial Tiamut.

619
00:56:59.129 --> 00:57:03.801
Every billion years.
new Celestials must be born.

620
00:57:04.385 --> 00:57:08.889
I plant Celestial seeds into host planets
across the universe.

621
00:57:11.016 --> 00:57:14.895
The planet Earth was chosen
to host the Celestial Tiamut.

622
00:57:20.276 --> 00:57:21.902
<i>In order to grow...</i>

623
00:57:22.069 --> 00:57:25.906
<i>Tiamut needs vast amounts of energy
from intelligent life.</i>

624
00:57:26.907 --> 00:57:30.411
<i>The Deviants prevented this
by consuming humans...</i>

625
00:57:30.578 --> 00:57:33.247
<i>until the Eternals eliminated them.</i>

626
00:57:33.873 --> 00:57:39.795
<i>Now. the human population of this planet
has reached the required amount.</i>

627
00:57:39.962 --> 00:57:43.007
<i>It is time for the emergence to begin.</i>

628
00:58:02.985 --> 00:58:04.069
But...

629
00:58:05.362 --> 00:58:07.114
everyone on Earth will die.

630
00:58:08.782 --> 00:58:11.869
The end of one life. Sersi...

631
00:58:13.245 --> 00:58:16.040
<i>is the beginning of another.</i>

632
00:58:28.886 --> 00:58:32.765
<i>Our universe
is a constant exchange of energy.</i>

633
00:58:33.766 --> 00:58:37.811
<i>An infinite cycle of creation
and destruction.</i>

634
00:58:38.729 --> 00:58:40.981
<i>Celestials use energy...</i>

635
00:58:41.148 --> 00:58:44.235
<i>gathered from host planets to create suns...</i>

636
00:58:44.902 --> 00:58:48.155
<i>generating gravity. heat. and light...</i>

637
00:58:48.322 --> 00:58:50.824
<i>for new galaxies to form.</i>

638
00:58:55.829 --> 00:58:57.456
<i>Without us...</i>

639
00:58:57.623 --> 00:59:00.793
<i>our universe will fall into darkness.</i>

640
00:59:03.546 --> 00:59:05.422
All life will die.

641
00:59:06.632 --> 00:59:08.384
Ajak knew the truth?

642
00:59:08.801 --> 00:59:13.681
She has helped many Celestials
to emerge over millions of years.

643
00:59:13.848 --> 00:59:15.558
So have you.

644
00:59:17.935 --> 00:59:19.812
Earth was my first mission.

645
00:59:21.689 --> 00:59:25.401
I was home. on Olympia.

646
00:59:26.777 --> 00:59:29.196
There is no Olympia.

647
00:59:47.298 --> 00:59:50.342
This is your true home. Sersi.

648
00:59:51.385 --> 00:59:53.095
The World Forge.

649
00:59:55.931 --> 01:00:00.186
It is here that I built
and programmed the Eternals.

650
01:00:36.180 --> 01:00:38.182
Everything dies except us...

651
01:00:39.475 --> 01:00:41.519
because we were never alive.

652
01:00:45.731 --> 01:00:47.525
Why don't I remember any of this?

653
01:00:57.952 --> 01:01:02.581
Because your memories are erased and reset
after each emergence.

654
01:01:03.707 --> 01:01:05.251
They are stored here.

655
01:01:07.962 --> 01:01:09.588
Why do you keep them?

656
01:01:10.256 --> 01:01:13.676
I keep them in order to study the Deviants.

657
01:01:14.802 --> 01:01:17.388
I created the Deviants. Sersi...

658
01:01:17.555 --> 01:01:20.474
for the same purpose I created you.

659
01:01:21.559 --> 01:01:25.396
<i>Every Celestial host planet
has its own predators.</i>

660
01:01:29.108 --> 01:01:32.278
<i>I first sent the Deviants
to exterminate them...</i>

661
01:01:32.444 --> 01:01:34.989
<i>so intelligent life could grow.</i>

662
01:01:40.536 --> 01:01:43.205
<i>But there was a flaw in their design.</i>

663
01:01:44.415 --> 01:01:45.749
<i>They evolved.</i>

664
01:01:45.916 --> 01:01:47.960
<i>Became predators themselves.</i>

665
01:01:49.920 --> 01:01:52.131
And I lost control of them.

666
01:01:54.216 --> 01:01:57.219
I built and programmed you. Eternals...

667
01:01:57.386 --> 01:02:01.223
to be synthetic beings
and incapable of evolution...

668
01:02:01.390 --> 01:02:03.559
to correct my mistake.

669
01:02:05.561 --> 01:02:09.982
Sersi. Ajak has chosen you
to take her place...

670
01:02:10.149 --> 01:02:12.401
as the Prime Eternal.

671
01:02:12.985 --> 01:02:14.778
Do not fail me.

672
01:02:33.255 --> 01:02:35.883
So. you're saying
we're basically fancy robots?

673
01:02:36.050 --> 01:02:39.345
And our past memories are stored somewhere...

674
01:02:40.137 --> 01:02:41.722
in space?

675
01:02:41.889 --> 01:02:44.225
And Arishem made the Deviants.

676
01:02:46.060 --> 01:02:47.811
I'm sorry. Thena.

677
01:02:47.978 --> 01:02:49.396
You tried to warn us.

678
01:02:49.563 --> 01:02:53.567
The last time Arishem reset your memories.
something must have gone wrong.

679
01:02:54.318 --> 01:02:55.361
What do you mean?

680
01:02:55.528 --> 01:02:58.864
Well. that's what Mahd Wy'ry is. isn't it?

681
01:02:59.031 --> 01:03:02.535
All this time. Thena was remembering
all the other planets we were sent to...

682
01:03:02.701 --> 01:03:04.787
and everyone dying during the emergence.

683
01:03:05.246 --> 01:03:06.705
I thought we were heroes.

684
01:03:07.373 --> 01:03:08.707
Turns out we're the bad guys.

685
01:03:08.874 --> 01:03:11.168
We're not the bad guys. okay?

686
01:03:11.335 --> 01:03:14.213
We've helped the Celestials
expand life across the universe.

687
01:03:14.380 --> 01:03:17.550
That's not what bad guys do.
That's what good guys do.

688
01:03:17.716 --> 01:03:20.636
Every time innocent lives
have been sacrificed for the greater good...

689
01:03:20.803 --> 01:03:22.847
it turns out to be a mistake.

690
01:03:23.472 --> 01:03:25.140
We have to stop the emergence.

691
01:03:25.307 --> 01:03:28.936
Sersi. we have no right
to stop the birth of a Celestial.

692
01:03:29.103 --> 01:03:31.981
There has to be a way Tiamut can emerge
without destroying the Earth.

693
01:03:33.065 --> 01:03:36.277
We just have to delay it
until we figure out how.

694
01:03:37.111 --> 01:03:39.321
Could Druig control its mind?

695
01:03:39.488 --> 01:03:41.740
Maybe put it to sleep?

696
01:03:41.907 --> 01:03:43.033
"Put it to sleep"?

697
01:03:43.492 --> 01:03:44.618
Are you serious?

698
01:03:44.785 --> 01:03:47.288
Gilgamesh asked Druig
to put me to sleep once.

699
01:03:48.622 --> 01:03:50.332
So I could take a vacation to Fiji. you know?

700
01:03:50.499 --> 01:03:53.210
-We're talking about a Celestial. okay?
-We have to try.

701
01:03:53.377 --> 01:03:56.714
Come on. we're not gonna let
everyone on Earth die. right?

702
01:03:56.881 --> 01:03:58.215
Right.

703
01:04:00.134 --> 01:04:03.053
I'm human. I'm a little biased.

704
01:04:07.558 --> 01:04:08.934
And do what?

705
01:04:09.560 --> 01:04:11.187
Watch TV?

706
01:04:11.353 --> 01:04:14.857
When I could be
with the Earth's original superheroes...

707
01:04:15.024 --> 01:04:17.443
as they try to save the world?

708
01:04:18.277 --> 01:04:19.486
Fine.

709
01:04:19.653 --> 01:04:22.198
If you want to. stay.

710
01:04:22.364 --> 01:04:24.116
Thank you very much. sir.

711
01:04:25.826 --> 01:04:27.036
Gilgamesh...

712
01:04:27.203 --> 01:04:28.746
could you please get rid of the saliva beer?

713
01:04:28.913 --> 01:04:30.206
I thought you liked it. man.

714
01:04:30.372 --> 01:04:32.374
We need to go. Now.

715
01:04:33.209 --> 01:04:34.585
Find the others.

716
01:04:34.919 --> 01:04:36.170
Once we're all together...

717
01:04:36.337 --> 01:04:39.048
we'll decide what to do about the emergence.

718
01:05:12.998 --> 01:05:14.583
It's very nice here. sir.

719
01:05:14.750 --> 01:05:16.043
Don't be fooled.

720
01:05:17.169 --> 01:05:19.255
Ignorance is bliss.

721
01:05:35.229 --> 01:05:36.438
Hello. Sprite.

722
01:05:44.280 --> 01:05:46.156
I missed all of you.

723
01:05:49.118 --> 01:05:53.038
Please. make yourselves at home.

724
01:05:57.877 --> 01:06:00.880
You've given me a lot of bad news
in one go. my lady.

725
01:06:01.630 --> 01:06:02.798
Will you help us?

726
01:06:03.299 --> 01:06:04.300
I am glad that...

727
01:06:11.432 --> 01:06:12.558
Hey. what's your service?

728
01:06:13.017 --> 01:06:14.518
I'm not getting any bars.

729
01:06:16.228 --> 01:06:19.565
Do you all remember this forest?
Beautiful.

730
01:06:20.733 --> 01:06:22.776
It was the last place we all lived together.

731
01:06:24.236 --> 01:06:27.198
I've protected these people
for 20 generations now...

732
01:06:27.364 --> 01:06:30.367
from the outside world and from themselves.

733
01:06:30.534 --> 01:06:35.247
Your kind. my friend. you will be responsible
for your own extinction one day.

734
01:06:35.789 --> 01:06:37.333
Don't you think?

735
01:06:37.791 --> 01:06:40.961
I think we must learn from our mistakes
and do better. sir.

736
01:06:41.128 --> 01:06:43.005
You must not give up hope.

737
01:06:45.925 --> 01:06:47.343
Oh. no. you didn't.

738
01:06:47.510 --> 01:06:50.012
Okay. new rule.
no more possessing people's valets.

739
01:06:50.179 --> 01:06:51.639
Where is your sense of humor. Kingo?

740
01:06:51.805 --> 01:06:52.806
I'm sorry. sir.

741
01:06:52.973 --> 01:06:55.184
Don't apologize. it's not your fault.

742
01:06:55.935 --> 01:06:58.562
You are not a god.
You know that. right?

743
01:06:58.729 --> 01:07:02.358
How ironic. Kingo. the movie star.

744
01:07:02.525 --> 01:07:04.109
I've directed some things. too.

745
01:07:04.276 --> 01:07:05.653
Oh. yeah? Like what?

746
01:07:06.278 --> 01:07:07.863
Some Internet content.

747
01:07:08.614 --> 01:07:09.615
How many views?

748
01:07:09.782 --> 01:07:11.700
I don't do it for the views.

749
01:07:11.867 --> 01:07:13.661
Let's go. He's wasting our time.

750
01:07:13.827 --> 01:07:16.121
-We need him.
-Ikaris.

751
01:07:17.164 --> 01:07:18.249
I missed you.

752
01:07:19.166 --> 01:07:21.252
Are you gonna charm me or threaten me?

753
01:07:21.418 --> 01:07:23.462
I mean. there's a third option.
if you prefer that.

754
01:07:23.629 --> 01:07:26.507
It must be heartbreaking to find out
that you're not Mother's favorite.

755
01:07:26.674 --> 01:07:28.342
And I'm sure she'd be real proud
of what you've been up to.

756
01:07:28.509 --> 01:07:29.510
Druig. this is serious.

757
01:07:29.677 --> 01:07:31.470
I'll tell you what's serious.

758
01:07:32.388 --> 01:07:36.350
I've just been told I've been sent on
a suicide mission for the past 7.000 years...

759
01:07:36.517 --> 01:07:39.895
and that my entire existence is a lie.

760
01:07:43.065 --> 01:07:46.402
So. excuse me for not giving a shit
about your plan right now.

761
01:07:51.282 --> 01:07:52.700
Druig sucks.

762
01:07:52.867 --> 01:07:54.493
He does. sir.

763
01:08:14.971 --> 01:08:16.724
I don't like this place.

764
01:08:17.183 --> 01:08:20.394
Druig needs to think.
and Sersi wants us to wait. so...

765
01:08:20.560 --> 01:08:21.770
we wait.

766
01:08:23.647 --> 01:08:27.484
I couldn't recognize myself
in Sprite's illusions.

767
01:08:28.569 --> 01:08:30.779
Those were the good old days.

768
01:08:32.656 --> 01:08:35.201
What if I can't fight anymore?

769
01:08:36.368 --> 01:08:37.912
Of course you can.

770
01:08:38.953 --> 01:08:40.997
What if I hurt you again?

771
01:08:41.372 --> 01:08:46.587
Come on. You know who you are.
You're Thena. goddess of war.

772
01:08:51.425 --> 01:08:52.843
Thank you.

773
01:08:54.303 --> 01:08:55.554
For what?

774
01:08:57.430 --> 01:08:59.642
For always taking care of me.

775
01:09:02.019 --> 01:09:03.729
I'd do it again.

776
01:09:06.564 --> 01:09:08.526
On any planet.

777
01:09:27.670 --> 01:09:29.129
I like watching him. too.

778
01:09:29.296 --> 01:09:30.464
Jeez.

779
01:09:31.590 --> 01:09:33.216
I don't think it's creepy at all.

780
01:09:35.845 --> 01:09:37.680
Have you read <i>Peter Pan?</i>

781
01:09:37.846 --> 01:09:40.975
Okay. so. to me. Ikaris is Peter...

782
01:09:41.140 --> 01:09:45.479
Sersi is Wendy. you are Tinker Bell.
for obvious reasons...

783
01:09:46.729 --> 01:09:49.108
and the rest of us are the Lost Boys.

784
01:09:49.567 --> 01:09:51.068
What's your point?

785
01:09:51.527 --> 01:09:54.071
Tinker Bell's always been in love with Peter.

786
01:09:57.491 --> 01:10:00.703
And it's hard for her
'cause she can never be with him.

787
01:10:03.622 --> 01:10:05.124
I'm sorry. Sprite.

788
01:10:07.042 --> 01:10:08.294
Kingo...

789
01:10:10.880 --> 01:10:13.382
why did Arishem make me this way?

790
01:10:15.467 --> 01:10:16.927
I don't know.

791
01:10:24.518 --> 01:10:25.895
I thought you broke it.

792
01:10:26.061 --> 01:10:27.855
Always bring backups.

793
01:10:32.985 --> 01:10:34.778
You have a very angry family. sir.

794
01:10:35.529 --> 01:10:37.406
Yeah. it's a big issue.

795
01:10:37.573 --> 01:10:40.492
<i>What about King Midas?
Everything he touched turned to gold.</i>

796
01:10:40.659 --> 01:10:41.660
<i>-Was that you?
</i>-Dane.

797
01:10:41.827 --> 01:10:43.746
<i>-Confucius? Aristotle?
</i>-Call your uncle.

798
01:10:43.913 --> 01:10:45.497
<i>What? My uncle? No.</i>

799
01:10:45.664 --> 01:10:47.833
You've always wanted
to make amends with him. right?

800
01:10:48.000 --> 01:10:50.377
Now is the time. Trust me.

801
01:10:50.544 --> 01:10:52.129
<i>Sersi. you're so weird.</i>

802
01:10:52.296 --> 01:10:53.547
Dane? Dane?

803
01:10:55.966 --> 01:10:57.426
You're breaking up.

804
01:10:57.593 --> 01:10:58.636
You're breaking up?

805
01:11:01.347 --> 01:11:02.973
How did he take the news?

806
01:11:03.390 --> 01:11:05.976
Couldn't bring myself to tell him
it was the end of the world.

807
01:11:06.143 --> 01:11:08.395
There's nothing he could do.

808
01:11:08.562 --> 01:11:09.563
Sersi.

809
01:11:12.942 --> 01:11:14.652
I'm worried about you.

810
01:11:15.653 --> 01:11:18.614
If Arishem finds out
you're trying to stop the emergence...

811
01:11:20.574 --> 01:11:23.494
I'm not powerful enough
to protect you from him.

812
01:11:29.041 --> 01:11:30.543
I'm not afraid.

813
01:11:31.794 --> 01:11:34.213
This violent cycle has to end.

814
01:11:38.717 --> 01:11:40.553
Hey. stop worrying about me.

815
01:11:41.637 --> 01:11:42.972
Old habit.

816
01:11:50.187 --> 01:11:52.273
Why did you leave?

817
01:11:54.066 --> 01:11:55.192
I told myself...

818
01:11:56.068 --> 01:11:58.070
something must have happened to you.

819
01:11:58.237 --> 01:12:00.239
So. I waited.

820
01:12:00.406 --> 01:12:02.867
Days became years...

821
01:12:03.033 --> 01:12:05.244
and you never came back.

822
01:12:07.121 --> 01:12:08.706
Sersi...

823
01:12:09.456 --> 01:12:11.292
I've missed you.

824
01:12:13.961 --> 01:12:15.963
I didn't want to leave.

825
01:12:19.049 --> 01:12:20.259
There's something I have to tell...

826
01:12:20.885 --> 01:12:22.094
Ikaris!

827
01:12:22.720 --> 01:12:23.929
Ikaris!

828
01:12:33.105 --> 01:12:34.607
Watch out!

829
01:12:34.773 --> 01:12:36.358
Clear the camp!

830
01:12:39.403 --> 01:12:40.738
Get behind me!

831
01:12:40.905 --> 01:12:41.906
One of them took Ikaris.

832
01:12:42.072 --> 01:12:43.240
It's an ambush!

833
01:12:52.666 --> 01:12:54.210
Very nice. sir!

834
01:12:54.543 --> 01:12:56.086
<i>Are you mental? Hide!</i>

835
01:12:56.253 --> 01:12:58.631
We need action sequences.

836
01:12:59.256 --> 01:13:00.466
Sir!

837
01:13:01.050 --> 01:13:02.843
Sprite. get Karun out of here.

838
01:13:05.095 --> 01:13:07.973
How many cameras did you bring. young man?

839
01:13:15.814 --> 01:13:17.233
Kingo!

840
01:13:17.399 --> 01:13:18.817
Come on!

841
01:13:25.533 --> 01:13:26.742
This way!

842
01:13:26.909 --> 01:13:28.077
Quickly! Come on!

843
01:13:33.207 --> 01:13:34.959
Get in! Get in!

844
01:14:12.913 --> 01:14:13.747
Ikaris!

845
01:14:29.346 --> 01:14:33.142
I've fought that one before.
It's stronger than the others.

846
01:14:36.270 --> 01:14:37.479
No.

847
01:14:39.523 --> 01:14:40.858
Terrible timing. Thena.

848
01:14:41.609 --> 01:14:42.693
Thena!

849
01:14:51.202 --> 01:14:52.453
Stop. Thena!

850
01:15:27.905 --> 01:15:29.031
Let them go.

851
01:15:29.198 --> 01:15:30.741
Now is not the time. Sersi.

852
01:15:30.908 --> 01:15:34.078
Please. I know you're better than this.

853
01:15:43.337 --> 01:15:44.463
Druig.

854
01:15:45.673 --> 01:15:47.675
Go! Get to the river!

855
01:16:05.234 --> 01:16:06.652
Gilgamesh.

856
01:16:07.319 --> 01:16:09.029
A little help here?

857
01:16:09.196 --> 01:16:10.322
Stay here.

858
01:16:10.990 --> 01:16:11.991
Say it.

859
01:16:13.409 --> 01:16:14.410
Stay here.

860
01:16:14.577 --> 01:16:16.662
Good. You're okay.

861
01:16:28.549 --> 01:16:29.884
They're headed for the camp.

862
01:16:30.050 --> 01:16:31.760
Go. They need you.

863
01:16:31.927 --> 01:16:33.345
Go. Ikaris.

864
01:16:41.353 --> 01:16:43.480
Sprite. buy me some time!

865
01:16:52.781 --> 01:16:54.575
Can you hurry up?

866
01:16:56.702 --> 01:16:57.620
Now!

867
01:17:02.416 --> 01:17:03.459
Dishoom.

868
01:17:13.010 --> 01:17:15.012
Karun! Did you get that?

869
01:17:15.179 --> 01:17:16.931
I did. sir!

870
01:17:52.007 --> 01:17:53.759
-Kingo!
-Just go.

871
01:17:53.926 --> 01:17:55.386
I'm not leaving you.

872
01:17:55.719 --> 01:17:56.762
Sprite!

873
01:18:31.463 --> 01:18:32.464
Ikaris!

874
01:19:15.132 --> 01:19:17.551
Sersi! Are you all right?

875
01:19:28.103 --> 01:19:29.813
How did you do that?

876
01:19:30.648 --> 01:19:32.399
I don't know.

877
01:19:45.538 --> 01:19:47.289
Stop. stop. stop.

878
01:19:49.208 --> 01:19:50.167
Thena.

879
01:20:33.043 --> 01:20:35.337
No. Gilgamesh.

880
01:20:35.838 --> 01:20:37.131
Stay back.

881
01:20:45.389 --> 01:20:46.807
Ajak...

882
01:20:48.434 --> 01:20:49.852
Her memories...

883
01:20:51.937 --> 01:20:53.939
I understand now.

884
01:20:55.065 --> 01:20:57.359
I can see what she saw.

885
01:20:58.611 --> 01:21:00.654
So many planets.

886
01:21:01.530 --> 01:21:07.036
So much life destroyed
every time a Celestial is born.

887
01:21:07.745 --> 01:21:09.622
Arishem used us...

888
01:21:09.788 --> 01:21:14.251
and left us to die with each emergence.

889
01:21:14.418 --> 01:21:16.045
We just wanted to survive.

890
01:21:18.506 --> 01:21:20.633
And then he sent you.

891
01:21:21.926 --> 01:21:26.096
I will kill you all
for what you have done to my kind.

892
01:21:26.263 --> 01:21:29.058
You are not saviors. Eternals.

893
01:21:29.600 --> 01:21:31.268
You are murderers.

894
01:21:34.939 --> 01:21:35.856
Ikaris!

895
01:21:50.913 --> 01:21:52.289
Thena.

896
01:21:55.292 --> 01:21:56.544
Hey.

897
01:21:58.504 --> 01:22:00.047
Remember.

898
01:22:08.347 --> 01:22:09.807
No.

899
01:22:11.684 --> 01:22:12.977
No.

900
01:22:16.480 --> 01:22:17.898
I'll remember.

901
01:22:18.065 --> 01:22:19.608
I'll remember.

902
01:22:42.548 --> 01:22:44.717
I'll remember.

903
01:23:27.134 --> 01:23:28.719
When I left...

904
01:23:28.886 --> 01:23:34.058
I thought about taking over the minds
of every human on this planet.

905
01:23:34.934 --> 01:23:38.270
Violence. fear. greed...

906
01:23:38.437 --> 01:23:39.980
all gone.

907
01:23:40.147 --> 01:23:41.315
Why didn't you?

908
01:23:41.482 --> 01:23:44.068
Because without their flaws...

909
01:23:44.610 --> 01:23:46.529
they wouldn't be human.

910
01:23:49.532 --> 01:23:52.535
Please. Druig. You can't stay here anymore.

911
01:23:53.285 --> 01:23:56.747
These Deviants are trying to keep us
from killing their own kind.

912
01:23:56.914 --> 01:23:59.750
They have a conscience now.
That makes them more dangerous.

913
01:23:59.917 --> 01:24:01.836
No. Sersi.

914
01:24:02.920 --> 01:24:05.339
That makes them us.

915
01:24:06.048 --> 01:24:08.008
Eternals and Deviants.

916
01:24:09.218 --> 01:24:10.845
Arishem's children.

917
01:24:12.012 --> 01:24:15.766
But you are asking me to take control
of a mind of a Celestial.

918
01:24:15.933 --> 01:24:19.186
I do not have that kind of power.

919
01:24:19.353 --> 01:24:21.063
We'll need Phastos.

920
01:24:23.607 --> 01:24:25.025
Well. good luck.

921
01:24:25.860 --> 01:24:28.779
He gave up on humans a long time ago.

922
01:25:01.437 --> 01:25:02.730
I did this.

923
01:25:04.648 --> 01:25:06.984
If my technology
hadn't helped them advance...

924
01:25:12.406 --> 01:25:14.283
Druig was right.

925
01:25:15.159 --> 01:25:17.244
Our mission was a mistake.

926
01:25:17.870 --> 01:25:19.455
These people...

927
01:25:21.248 --> 01:25:22.499
they're not worth saving.

928
01:25:22.666 --> 01:25:24.502
Oh. Phastos.

929
01:25:24.668 --> 01:25:26.128
They're not worth saving.

930
01:25:38.307 --> 01:25:40.059
-Thanks.
-Give me a good one.

931
01:25:40.226 --> 01:25:41.602
-All right.
-Over here.

932
01:25:41.769 --> 01:25:42.686
And...

933
01:25:43.354 --> 01:25:44.396
-Oh. that's great. man!
-Yeah!

934
01:25:44.563 --> 01:25:45.689
-Yeah!
-Oh. yeah!

935
01:25:45.856 --> 01:25:47.525
-Nice.
-Good one. All right. ready? Throw!

936
01:25:48.817 --> 01:25:49.652
So close.

937
01:25:49.818 --> 01:25:50.903
-Daddy. Daddy. watch this.
-Yeah. okay.

938
01:25:51.070 --> 01:25:53.030
-Watch this.
-Let me see. Let me see it.

939
01:25:54.198 --> 01:25:55.741
Dad. I'm only a starter.

940
01:25:55.908 --> 01:25:56.909
Hi.

941
01:25:57.076 --> 01:25:58.369
Hello. Can we help you?

942
01:25:58.536 --> 01:25:59.453
Throw it again.

943
01:25:59.620 --> 01:26:02.206
Hey. Jack. Ben.

944
01:26:03.415 --> 01:26:06.794
Hey. guys.
These are my friends from college.

945
01:26:09.129 --> 01:26:14.176
This is Sylvia and Isaac.
That's Isaac.

946
01:26:14.635 --> 01:26:16.679
-Isaac.
-Dad. that's Superman.

947
01:26:16.846 --> 01:26:19.265
-Dad. that's Superman!
-Jack... That's really funny. Jack.

948
01:26:19.431 --> 01:26:21.392
-No. no! He is Superman.
-That is definitely not Superman.

949
01:26:21.559 --> 01:26:25.479
I saw him on TV.
He was in London. fighting a monster.

950
01:26:26.105 --> 01:26:29.525
And you were with a cape and you were
shooting laser beams out of your eyes.

951
01:26:30.234 --> 01:26:31.235
I don't wear a cape.

952
01:26:31.402 --> 01:26:33.654
-Oh. sorry.
-Okay. well. we should just go inside. right?

953
01:26:33.821 --> 01:26:36.323
Can I call you Clark? Is that what you
go by now? Because. you know...

954
01:26:36.490 --> 01:26:38.117
You've called me worse.

955
01:26:38.284 --> 01:26:39.827
You got it. Jack?

956
01:26:39.994 --> 01:26:41.078
Way to go.

957
01:26:41.245 --> 01:26:43.289
-Yes.
-All right. Show me how it's done.

958
01:26:43.664 --> 01:26:46.250
Round and round and round
and round and round.

959
01:26:49.753 --> 01:26:51.463
-Yep. you got it. Keep going.
-Come on.

960
01:27:00.222 --> 01:27:03.184
Yeah. Incredibly natural. guys.

961
01:27:05.936 --> 01:27:08.022
So. after all these years...

962
01:27:08.189 --> 01:27:10.274
even you fell for Ajak's lies.

963
01:27:10.441 --> 01:27:11.942
No need to rub it in.

964
01:27:13.944 --> 01:27:17.990
It all makes sense why she wouldn't let us
interfere with human conflicts.

965
01:27:18.532 --> 01:27:20.201
Conflicts lead to war...

966
01:27:20.367 --> 01:27:24.955
and war actually leads to advancement
in lifesaving technology and medicine.

967
01:27:25.122 --> 01:27:27.124
So our mission was never to...

968
01:27:27.291 --> 01:27:30.044
make a peaceful or harmonious world...

969
01:27:30.211 --> 01:27:33.964
but to increase the population at all costs.

970
01:27:34.131 --> 01:27:37.176
Just farming humans as food
for the Celestials. right?

971
01:27:37.343 --> 01:27:38.344
That's bleak.

972
01:27:38.511 --> 01:27:40.012
Well. so is telling
your husband and your child...

973
01:27:40.179 --> 01:27:41.764
that they could be dead within a few days.

974
01:27:41.931 --> 01:27:44.016
Thought you'd given up on humans.

975
01:27:44.767 --> 01:27:46.727
I got lucky. Okay?

976
01:27:48.979 --> 01:27:51.023
I have a family now.

977
01:27:51.190 --> 01:27:53.526
They've given me faith again.

978
01:27:54.610 --> 01:27:58.697
And I see the good in humanity in them
every single day.

979
01:27:58.864 --> 01:28:00.491
So. look. I cannot help you.

980
01:28:00.658 --> 01:28:01.784
-I am never leaving them.
-Phastos...

981
01:28:01.951 --> 01:28:03.035
I'm sorry. Sersi.

982
01:28:03.202 --> 01:28:04.578
It was wrong for me to use my powers...

983
01:28:04.745 --> 01:28:06.664
without thinking about the consequences
in the first place.

984
01:28:06.830 --> 01:28:11.585
So. now. I choose to use my hands
to fix my child's bicycle. okay?

985
01:28:12.127 --> 01:28:13.337
Do you?

986
01:28:14.380 --> 01:28:15.589
I don't use my powers anymore.

987
01:28:15.756 --> 01:28:17.091
You sure?

988
01:28:17.258 --> 01:28:18.092
What are you...

989
01:28:21.679 --> 01:28:25.015
What the hell is wrong with you?
My child is right down the hallway!

990
01:28:25.182 --> 01:28:27.184
That looks like someone's
been using his powers.

991
01:28:27.351 --> 01:28:29.562
-Oh. my God.
-I bet you've built the perfect safe house.

992
01:28:29.728 --> 01:28:31.272
What is this even made of? Vibranium?

993
01:28:31.438 --> 01:28:32.356
Don't!

994
01:28:36.569 --> 01:28:38.070
Fall collection.

995
01:28:38.237 --> 01:28:39.488
IKEA.

996
01:28:39.655 --> 01:28:40.656
Ass.

997
01:28:40.823 --> 01:28:43.534
How did you even deal with this guy
for over 5.000 years?

998
01:28:43.701 --> 01:28:46.287
If you stay here. you might as well
invite the Deviants to dinner.

999
01:28:46.453 --> 01:28:47.997
Never mind waiting for the end of the world.

1000
01:28:48.163 --> 01:28:49.415
He has a point.

1001
01:28:49.582 --> 01:28:52.585
No. I'm sorry. You can't just show up
in my life and expect me to go with you.

1002
01:28:52.751 --> 01:28:54.753
-I'm not gonna...
-You should go. <i>habibi.</i>

1003
01:28:55.546 --> 01:28:56.839
You want me to go?

1004
01:28:57.006 --> 01:28:59.800
You know what my mom would say to you
right now. right?

1005
01:29:04.180 --> 01:29:05.472
He's a chronic procrastinator.

1006
01:29:05.639 --> 01:29:07.600
I'm not leaving you two. No way.

1007
01:29:07.766 --> 01:29:09.560
I'm not happy about it...

1008
01:29:10.227 --> 01:29:13.480
but if there's a chance for us to watch Jack
grow up to live a life of his own...

1009
01:29:13.647 --> 01:29:15.357
we should take it.

1010
01:30:43.696 --> 01:30:45.531
The <i>Domo.</i>

1011
01:30:46.699 --> 01:30:48.200
Wow.

1012
01:30:58.043 --> 01:31:01.130
<i>A foreboding atmosphere fills the air.</i>

1013
01:31:01.964 --> 01:31:04.842
<i>An eerie stillness chokes our lungs.</i>

1014
01:31:05.009 --> 01:31:07.595
<i>What are you doing? You know you're
creeping us out. You know that. right?</i>

1015
01:31:08.262 --> 01:31:10.681
<i>Oh. God! Stay calm. T. please!</i>

1016
01:31:14.476 --> 01:31:16.854
<i>Chips. It's just chips.</i>

1017
01:31:17.271 --> 01:31:21.442
<i>As you can see. being an Eternal does not
preclude you from having human emotions...</i>

1018
01:31:21.609 --> 01:31:23.402
<i>such as cowardice.</i>

1019
01:31:25.905 --> 01:31:27.489
What has she done?

1020
01:31:27.990 --> 01:31:31.327
Is that... a sarcophagus in my lab?

1021
01:31:32.620 --> 01:31:35.873
This is Makkari.
Or should I say Miss Havisham?

1022
01:31:36.040 --> 01:31:37.750
None of us have seen her for centuries.

1023
01:32:01.690 --> 01:32:02.733
Is that the Ebony Blade?

1024
01:32:02.900 --> 01:32:04.151
Excalibur.

1025
01:32:05.694 --> 01:32:07.279
Arthur always did have a crush on you.

1026
01:32:18.374 --> 01:32:21.544
That. and the world is ending.

1027
01:32:26.048 --> 01:32:27.299
Have you seen my movies?

1028
01:32:31.095 --> 01:32:32.096
DVD?

1029
01:32:32.471 --> 01:32:34.014
It's all about streaming now.

1030
01:32:34.181 --> 01:32:36.100
You know. what you need is a Kindle.

1031
01:32:36.267 --> 01:32:38.310
Do you know what that is?
It's like a...

1032
01:32:38.936 --> 01:32:41.730
You know. I just realized
that if you don't know what an iPad is...

1033
01:32:41.897 --> 01:32:44.024
there's almost no way to explain it.

1034
01:32:48.237 --> 01:32:52.575
So. how did you end up scoring
this Emerald Tablet...

1035
01:32:52.741 --> 01:32:55.661
my beautiful. beautiful Makkari?

1036
01:32:58.747 --> 01:33:00.124
Did you miss me?

1037
01:33:01.333 --> 01:33:02.877
I'm sorry. what are we watching?
Because this...

1038
01:33:03.043 --> 01:33:05.129
-Is this new? Because I hate it.
-Are you two...

1039
01:33:05.296 --> 01:33:08.257
Phastos. I need to control
the mind of a Celestial.

1040
01:33:08.424 --> 01:33:09.884
Okay. get ready for it.

1041
01:33:13.179 --> 01:33:14.305
Bracelets?

1042
01:33:14.805 --> 01:33:15.890
You made us bracelets?

1043
01:33:16.056 --> 01:33:17.975
So. here's a little Celestial 101.

1044
01:33:18.142 --> 01:33:21.812
Celestials are the most powerful
energy generators in the universe.

1045
01:33:21.979 --> 01:33:25.232
When Arishem made us.
he imbued us with infinite cosmic energy...

1046
01:33:25.441 --> 01:33:28.569
to keep our bodies regenerating.
The bracelets. in theory...

1047
01:33:28.736 --> 01:33:30.696
shut down our regeneration process.

1048
01:33:30.863 --> 01:33:33.949
And once that happens.
our bodies accumulate extra cosmic energy.

1049
01:33:34.283 --> 01:33:35.284
What for?

1050
01:33:35.451 --> 01:33:38.245
Well. if the Deviants
can absorb our energy...

1051
01:33:38.787 --> 01:33:42.082
what if we can absorb
each other's energy as well?

1052
01:33:42.249 --> 01:33:44.752
If I can find a way to connect us all...

1053
01:33:44.919 --> 01:33:46.879
one of us could become immensely powerful...

1054
01:33:47.046 --> 01:33:49.757
pulling the accumulated energy
from the rest...

1055
01:33:49.924 --> 01:33:51.091
forming...

1056
01:33:54.678 --> 01:33:56.055
a Uni-Mind.

1057
01:33:59.808 --> 01:34:01.769
"Uni" meaning "one." "mind" meaning "mind."

1058
01:34:01.936 --> 01:34:02.937
Oh. no. we heard you the first time.

1059
01:34:03.103 --> 01:34:04.396
-Terrible name.
-We'll brainstorm...

1060
01:34:05.064 --> 01:34:06.065
"Brainstorm"!

1061
01:34:06.232 --> 01:34:07.733
-That's a way better name!
-No. I invented it...

1062
01:34:07.900 --> 01:34:08.901
so I'm calling it whatever I want.

1063
01:34:14.865 --> 01:34:17.284
We find humans a new home on another planet.

1064
01:34:17.451 --> 01:34:20.287
Are we building a big ship. too?
Take a pair of each animal?

1065
01:34:20.454 --> 01:34:22.831
Well. you know what's never saved the planet?
Your sarcasm.

1066
01:34:22.998 --> 01:34:24.834
Space colonization could take decades.

1067
01:34:25.000 --> 01:34:26.377
It can happen quickly with our help.

1068
01:34:26.544 --> 01:34:28.963
What if we end up
accidentally killing Tiamut?

1069
01:34:29.129 --> 01:34:32.883
We could be responsible for billions of lives
not being created across the universe.

1070
01:34:33.050 --> 01:34:34.385
Boss. am I right?

1071
01:34:36.053 --> 01:34:37.805
Say something. Ikaris.

1072
01:34:37.972 --> 01:34:39.640
You don't think we should be doing this.

1073
01:34:46.397 --> 01:34:48.774
Ajak chose Sersi to lead us.

1074
01:34:50.234 --> 01:34:52.111
Sersi should decide.

1075
01:34:54.738 --> 01:34:56.532
Forget who Ajak chose.

1076
01:34:56.699 --> 01:34:59.869
You're the strongest.
You should be making this decision.

1077
01:35:00.953 --> 01:35:03.247
Fine. Just keep lying to yourself.

1078
01:35:03.414 --> 01:35:04.790
Sprite.

1079
01:35:13.924 --> 01:35:15.176
Okay. this is not...

1080
01:35:15.342 --> 01:35:16.635
-Ikaris.
-Don't run after him.

1081
01:35:16.802 --> 01:35:18.804
Kingo. I...
You guys.

1082
01:35:19.221 --> 01:35:21.682
Hey. Don't sweat it.
Sprite's always cranky.

1083
01:35:21.849 --> 01:35:23.726
I used to hear her complaining
even when she wasn't there.

1084
01:35:23.893 --> 01:35:25.227
I'm okay. Kingo.

1085
01:35:25.394 --> 01:35:27.104
If you think we should do this. I trust you.

1086
01:35:27.271 --> 01:35:29.940
I will follow you to the end.
like I always have.

1087
01:35:31.942 --> 01:35:33.444
What did you say?

1088
01:35:33.694 --> 01:35:36.155
I will follow you to the end.
like I always have.

1089
01:35:37.907 --> 01:35:40.784
I'm not who you think I am.

1090
01:36:19.114 --> 01:36:20.741
How long do we have?

1091
01:36:21.158 --> 01:36:22.743
Seven days.

1092
01:36:23.285 --> 01:36:24.578
Good.

1093
01:36:26.163 --> 01:36:28.165
We completed our mission.

1094
01:36:31.001 --> 01:36:32.545
Where is she?

1095
01:36:32.711 --> 01:36:33.712
London.

1096
01:36:34.547 --> 01:36:36.131
She has a good life there.

1097
01:36:36.298 --> 01:36:38.384
I'm sure she's missed you.

1098
01:36:38.551 --> 01:36:41.846
If I'd gone back to her.
I would only have told her the truth.

1099
01:36:43.681 --> 01:36:45.307
She would've suffered...

1100
01:36:45.474 --> 01:36:47.977
knowing this world she loves
would end one day.

1101
01:36:48.143 --> 01:36:49.311
Ikaris.

1102
01:36:50.354 --> 01:36:52.022
We have to tell them the truth.

1103
01:36:52.189 --> 01:36:53.607
What?

1104
01:36:53.983 --> 01:36:55.526
-Why?
-Because together...

1105
01:36:55.693 --> 01:36:57.778
we might be able to stop the emergence.

1106
01:36:58.529 --> 01:37:00.197
"Stop the emergence"?

1107
01:37:00.364 --> 01:37:01.365
Listen...

1108
01:37:01.532 --> 01:37:03.367
-Ajak. I know it's hard at the end...
-Listen to me. Ikaris.

1109
01:37:03.534 --> 01:37:06.579
I have followed Arishem
for millions of years.

1110
01:37:06.745 --> 01:37:09.373
And I have never doubted him.

1111
01:37:09.540 --> 01:37:11.208
-Until now.
-Why now?

1112
01:37:12.168 --> 01:37:13.544
Why now?

1113
01:37:18.424 --> 01:37:23.053
Five years ago. Thanos erased
half of the population of the universe.

1114
01:37:24.513 --> 01:37:26.348
Delayed the emergence.

1115
01:37:28.392 --> 01:37:30.352
But the people of this planet...

1116
01:37:30.519 --> 01:37:33.772
brought everyone back
with the snap of a finger.

1117
01:37:34.982 --> 01:37:38.110
You know. after I let you all go...

1118
01:37:38.277 --> 01:37:41.155
I traveled the world. living among them.

1119
01:37:41.322 --> 01:37:44.909
I have seen them fight and lie and kill...

1120
01:37:45.201 --> 01:37:47.536
but I have also seen them...

1121
01:37:47.703 --> 01:37:50.122
laugh and love.

1122
01:37:50.289 --> 01:37:54.293
I've seen them create and dream.

1123
01:37:57.505 --> 01:37:58.881
This planet...

1124
01:37:59.548 --> 01:38:01.133
and these people...

1125
01:38:02.593 --> 01:38:04.261
have changed me.

1126
01:38:05.846 --> 01:38:09.892
The cost of Arishem's design.
it's not worth it.

1127
01:38:10.059 --> 01:38:11.685
Not this time.

1128
01:38:13.521 --> 01:38:15.231
I trust you. Ajak.

1129
01:38:19.485 --> 01:38:21.320
I'll follow you to the end...

1130
01:38:22.655 --> 01:38:24.156
as I always have.

1131
01:38:24.323 --> 01:38:25.699
Thank you.

1132
01:38:27.326 --> 01:38:29.286
We have to bring everyone back together.

1133
01:38:31.914 --> 01:38:34.250
There's something I have to show you first.

1134
01:38:44.885 --> 01:38:46.554
It's just up ahead.

1135
01:38:54.061 --> 01:38:56.564
They must have been trapped in the ice
for centuries...

1136
01:38:56.730 --> 01:38:59.650
and broke free last week
when the glacier started to melt...

1137
01:38:59.817 --> 01:39:02.528
as the Earth's core heats up
for the emergence.

1138
01:39:03.737 --> 01:39:06.073
They killed an entire company of oil workers.

1139
01:39:06.866 --> 01:39:08.492
I tracked them here.

1140
01:39:11.996 --> 01:39:14.331
I suspected you might have changed your mind.

1141
01:39:15.499 --> 01:39:17.543
I can't let you betray Arishem.

1142
01:39:19.253 --> 01:39:21.338
Why don't you just kill me yourself?

1143
01:39:21.505 --> 01:39:24.508
When the others realize
something is happening to the Earth...

1144
01:39:25.176 --> 01:39:26.343
they'll come to you.

1145
01:39:27.052 --> 01:39:29.930
When they find your body.
they'll know the Deviants are back.

1146
01:39:30.347 --> 01:39:33.017
It'll keep them busy until the emergence.

1147
01:39:34.727 --> 01:39:37.062
I've been loyal to you. Ajak.

1148
01:39:37.396 --> 01:39:39.857
Kept your secret for centuries...

1149
01:39:40.191 --> 01:39:42.943
lied to everyone I cared about...

1150
01:39:43.110 --> 01:39:47.740
but never have I doubted my purpose
to serve the Celestials.

1151
01:39:48.449 --> 01:39:50.367
Oh. Ikaris.

1152
01:39:55.247 --> 01:39:58.125
I've led you down the wrong path.

1153
01:39:58.918 --> 01:40:00.336
It's the only path I know.

1154
01:42:54.093 --> 01:42:56.053
Thought I'd find you here.

1155
01:42:56.554 --> 01:42:58.973
I've thought about this place a lot.

1156
01:43:00.182 --> 01:43:02.518
Amazing how things change over time.

1157
01:43:03.102 --> 01:43:05.229
Maybe we're the ones who've changed.

1158
01:43:08.065 --> 01:43:09.942
I know you don't agree with our plan.

1159
01:43:11.068 --> 01:43:14.071
I've always thought of the Celestials
like the ocean.

1160
01:43:15.906 --> 01:43:19.410
They give life
and they take life away without bias.

1161
01:43:19.827 --> 01:43:22.538
If they were gone.
this universe would eventually end.

1162
01:43:23.038 --> 01:43:25.457
What you're trying to do is free humanity
from the natural order.

1163
01:43:25.624 --> 01:43:29.461
It's not natural to allow all life
on an entire planet to be destroyed.

1164
01:43:30.171 --> 01:43:31.922
Arishem's way is archaic and violent.

1165
01:43:32.089 --> 01:43:34.049
I don't want to fight. Sersi.

1166
01:43:34.842 --> 01:43:35.843
It'll all end soon.

1167
01:43:36.010 --> 01:43:38.846
Except there is no end. is there?

1168
01:43:39.096 --> 01:43:41.599
We'd carry on without our memories...

1169
01:43:41.765 --> 01:43:43.309
or free will...

1170
01:43:43.475 --> 01:43:45.060
for eternity.

1171
01:43:50.774 --> 01:43:52.151
You're afraid.

1172
01:43:52.568 --> 01:43:55.196
I wouldn't mind leaving this world.

1173
01:43:55.905 --> 01:43:57.865
I only wish that when we do...

1174
01:43:59.450 --> 01:44:01.702
I would be able to remember you.

1175
01:44:03.787 --> 01:44:06.248
I'm in love with you. Sersi.

1176
01:44:06.707 --> 01:44:09.627
I'm grateful for the life
I've lived with you.

1177
01:44:15.799 --> 01:44:16.884
Ikaris.

1178
01:44:41.742 --> 01:44:43.035
Sersi?

1179
01:44:47.039 --> 01:44:48.499
It's started.

1180
01:44:51.961 --> 01:44:53.629
Oh. no. My God.

1181
01:44:54.213 --> 01:44:55.214
What about the Uni-Mind?

1182
01:44:55.673 --> 01:44:58.425
I haven't figured out a way to connect us.
but I'm close.

1183
01:44:58.592 --> 01:45:00.135
-I'm very. very close.
-How much longer?

1184
01:45:00.302 --> 01:45:02.304
I don't know. Sersi!

1185
01:45:05.516 --> 01:45:06.851
Find the point of emergence.

1186
01:45:30.749 --> 01:45:33.335
You always knew the end was coming.

1187
01:45:33.502 --> 01:45:36.130
It must be a relief.

1188
01:45:36.297 --> 01:45:38.299
That Deviant is still tracking us.

1189
01:45:39.008 --> 01:45:41.552
Revenge won't bring peace for you. Thena.

1190
01:45:42.052 --> 01:45:44.263
But killing it might.

1191
01:45:57.359 --> 01:45:58.777
Ikaris?

1192
01:46:00.196 --> 01:46:01.655
What are you doing?

1193
01:46:07.620 --> 01:46:10.247
I wanted you to leave this world in peace.

1194
01:46:11.624 --> 01:46:14.043
Without knowing about the emergence.

1195
01:46:14.418 --> 01:46:16.003
But I failed.

1196
01:46:19.840 --> 01:46:21.550
I wish Ajak hadn't chosen you.

1197
01:46:28.766 --> 01:46:30.100
I'm close to figuring it out.

1198
01:46:34.605 --> 01:46:35.898
Boss. what are you doing?

1199
01:46:36.065 --> 01:46:37.566
I've let this go on long enough.

1200
01:46:37.733 --> 01:46:38.651
Don't hurt him!

1201
01:46:40.778 --> 01:46:42.363
He lied to us.

1202
01:46:43.239 --> 01:46:44.990
He already knew about the emergence.

1203
01:46:45.699 --> 01:46:47.034
No. he didn't.

1204
01:46:47.201 --> 01:46:49.912
Ajak told me everything when we left Babylon.

1205
01:46:51.288 --> 01:46:52.289
What?

1206
01:46:53.290 --> 01:46:55.668
You were never gonna let us
stop the emergence.

1207
01:46:55.835 --> 01:46:56.836
No.

1208
01:46:58.128 --> 01:47:00.798
I only wanted to protect you
from the Deviants.

1209
01:47:00.965 --> 01:47:04.260
If Ajak wanted you to take her place.
why did she choose me?

1210
01:47:09.390 --> 01:47:10.641
What have you done?

1211
01:47:11.976 --> 01:47:13.602
He killed her.

1212
01:47:16.355 --> 01:47:17.356
I had to.

1213
01:47:18.774 --> 01:47:20.651
She loved you.

1214
01:47:23.445 --> 01:47:25.114
-Did she?
-She loved you.

1215
01:47:27.491 --> 01:47:29.827
Do you think it was easy
to live with the truth?

1216
01:47:30.828 --> 01:47:32.830
To know that one day all this would end?

1217
01:47:34.957 --> 01:47:37.334
To keep on lying to you?

1218
01:47:38.794 --> 01:47:40.880
If we gave humanity the choice...

1219
01:47:41.046 --> 01:47:46.135
how many of them would be willing to die
so that billions more could be born?

1220
01:47:46.302 --> 01:47:48.679
We're not giving them a choice.

1221
01:47:49.471 --> 01:47:52.808
Is this why you're willing to kill?

1222
01:47:53.809 --> 01:47:56.478
You are so pathetic!

1223
01:47:56.896 --> 01:47:59.190
I'm an Eternal. Phastos.

1224
01:47:59.815 --> 01:48:02.860
I exist for Arishem.

1225
01:48:03.027 --> 01:48:04.278
As do you.

1226
01:48:04.778 --> 01:48:05.779
It's who you are.

1227
01:48:05.946 --> 01:48:10.618
I wouldn't change a single thing
about who I am.

1228
01:48:10.784 --> 01:48:12.745
Born or made.

1229
01:48:12.912 --> 01:48:15.164
But I do not exist for Arishem...

1230
01:48:15.331 --> 01:48:17.291
I exist for my family!

1231
01:48:17.458 --> 01:48:19.919
Then you are making
the same mistake Ajak did.

1232
01:48:22.963 --> 01:48:24.173
-No!
-Makkari!

1233
01:48:26.509 --> 01:48:27.968
Get out of here!

1234
01:48:31.013 --> 01:48:32.389
Kingo.

1235
01:48:40.314 --> 01:48:42.900
You do not turn against your family.

1236
01:48:43.817 --> 01:48:46.195
Gilgamesh died because of you.

1237
01:48:48.113 --> 01:48:49.573
You won't succeed against me.

1238
01:48:50.574 --> 01:48:53.160
And I will kill every one of you
if I have to.

1239
01:49:00.918 --> 01:49:02.044
Wait.

1240
01:49:03.003 --> 01:49:04.046
I'm going with you.

1241
01:49:04.213 --> 01:49:05.256
Sprite...

1242
01:49:07.049 --> 01:49:08.092
What is this?

1243
01:49:25.609 --> 01:49:27.444
Because she loves him.

1244
01:49:29.238 --> 01:49:31.699
Oh. you guys didn't pick up on that?

1245
01:49:32.867 --> 01:49:35.035
He really fooled us. didn't he?

1246
01:49:35.911 --> 01:49:37.204
Karun. let's go.

1247
01:49:37.746 --> 01:49:38.956
Wait. where the hell are you going?

1248
01:49:39.123 --> 01:49:41.041
I can't help you guys.

1249
01:49:42.084 --> 01:49:43.711
I still think Ikaris is right.

1250
01:49:43.878 --> 01:49:46.922
So. that's it. huh? Just gonna follow him?

1251
01:49:47.715 --> 01:49:49.717
I love the people of this planet.

1252
01:49:50.176 --> 01:49:52.469
But if you stop this emergence...

1253
01:49:52.636 --> 01:49:55.014
you are preventing
so many other worlds like this one...

1254
01:49:55.181 --> 01:49:56.765
from being created.

1255
01:49:57.474 --> 01:49:59.310
I still have faith in Arishem.

1256
01:49:59.768 --> 01:50:02.938
But I refuse to hurt any of you
for my beliefs.

1257
01:50:08.903 --> 01:50:11.488
Even with my help. we're no match.

1258
01:50:12.239 --> 01:50:13.908
It's Ikaris.

1259
01:50:17.286 --> 01:50:18.287
But...

1260
01:50:19.079 --> 01:50:20.956
I hope to see you on the next planet.

1261
01:50:48.609 --> 01:50:49.610
Look...

1262
01:50:50.319 --> 01:50:53.322
if I'm gonna get myself killed
going up against Ikaris...

1263
01:50:54.114 --> 01:50:55.991
we'll need to have a backup plan.

1264
01:50:56.158 --> 01:50:57.868
All of our powers.
even if they're amplified...

1265
01:50:58.035 --> 01:50:59.411
are not enough to kill a Celestial. so...

1266
01:50:59.578 --> 01:51:02.122
Well. Sersi did turn a Deviant into a tree.

1267
01:51:03.123 --> 01:51:04.250
I'm sorry. what?

1268
01:51:04.917 --> 01:51:06.377
You didn't wanna tell me that?

1269
01:51:08.420 --> 01:51:09.839
I don't know how it happened. okay?

1270
01:51:10.005 --> 01:51:12.424
And I'm pretty sure I couldn't do it again.

1271
01:51:12.591 --> 01:51:15.135
Well. now is the time to try.
don't you think?

1272
01:51:15.302 --> 01:51:17.263
Phastos. that Deviant is dead.

1273
01:51:17.429 --> 01:51:20.641
Our plan is to put Tiamut to sleep.
not to kill it.

1274
01:51:20.808 --> 01:51:22.184
I can't kill a Celestial.

1275
01:51:22.351 --> 01:51:23.978
Sersi. Sersi.

1276
01:51:24.144 --> 01:51:25.521
We can't!

1277
01:51:31.485 --> 01:51:32.611
We can't.

1278
01:51:32.778 --> 01:51:34.321
It's okay. Sersi.

1279
01:51:35.656 --> 01:51:37.032
I got this.

1280
01:51:53.257 --> 01:51:54.884
There's no time for that.

1281
01:51:56.051 --> 01:51:58.762
I didn't see the lies right in front of me.

1282
01:52:00.055 --> 01:52:02.933
I'm not even sure why Ajak chose me to lead.

1283
01:52:04.476 --> 01:52:06.020
I asked Gilgamesh once...

1284
01:52:06.520 --> 01:52:08.856
why he chose to protect me.

1285
01:52:09.273 --> 01:52:10.691
He said...

1286
01:52:11.150 --> 01:52:14.486
"When you love something. you protect it.

1287
01:52:15.196 --> 01:52:19.825
"It is the most natural thing in the world."

1288
01:52:22.494 --> 01:52:27.041
You have loved these people
since the day we arrived.

1289
01:52:28.459 --> 01:52:33.881
So. there is no one better
to lead us now than you.

1290
01:52:36.383 --> 01:52:37.676
Sersi.

1291
01:52:39.929 --> 01:52:41.263
Get up.

1292
01:52:49.188 --> 01:52:51.649
Ajak chose you for a reason.

1293
01:52:56.904 --> 01:52:57.863
Sersi!

1294
01:52:58.322 --> 01:52:59.365
Sersi!

1295
01:52:59.532 --> 01:53:01.116
Sersi. We need you!

1296
01:53:01.283 --> 01:53:02.826
I already gave that speech.

1297
01:53:02.993 --> 01:53:04.036
What?

1298
01:53:04.203 --> 01:53:05.454
You did... What...

1299
01:53:05.621 --> 01:53:08.624
Sersi. the sphere inside of you...

1300
01:53:08.791 --> 01:53:10.334
it creates a connection
between you and Arishem.

1301
01:53:10.501 --> 01:53:13.629
Maybe I can repurpose it...

1302
01:53:13.796 --> 01:53:16.048
and create a connection between...

1303
01:53:16.549 --> 01:53:17.550
well. all of us.

1304
01:53:18.008 --> 01:53:20.302
And that can activate the Uni-Mind.

1305
01:53:20.469 --> 01:53:22.137
-Great.
-Yeah.

1306
01:53:22.847 --> 01:53:24.098
But...

1307
01:53:25.140 --> 01:53:26.976
I have to take it out of you.

1308
01:53:29.895 --> 01:53:31.105
Okay.

1309
01:53:32.606 --> 01:53:33.691
Do it.

1310
01:53:35.317 --> 01:53:36.443
Okay.

1311
01:53:44.451 --> 01:53:46.036
Don't kill her.

1312
01:53:46.203 --> 01:53:47.413
Thena...

1313
01:53:48.664 --> 01:53:49.707
Do it.

1314
01:54:03.387 --> 01:54:04.680
Will it work?

1315
01:54:09.393 --> 01:54:10.811
It has to.

1316
01:55:02.613 --> 01:55:04.406
I'm glad you're here.

1317
01:55:08.619 --> 01:55:10.204
Thank you. Sprite.

1318
01:55:25.052 --> 01:55:26.720
Protect the emergence.

1319
01:55:26.887 --> 01:55:28.639
You're really gonna kill them?

1320
01:55:36.480 --> 01:55:38.023
Where's Druig?

1321
01:55:38.566 --> 01:55:39.775
He's busy.

1322
01:55:39.942 --> 01:55:42.027
Thena. play nice.

1323
01:55:45.823 --> 01:55:47.241
You've never had to fight me.

1324
01:55:47.408 --> 01:55:48.534
But I've always wanted to.

1325
01:55:56.959 --> 01:55:59.170
It's time to put a god to sleep.

1326
01:57:06.612 --> 01:57:08.447
I should've done this five centuries ago.

1327
01:57:55.786 --> 01:57:57.288
Druig's gone.

1328
01:57:58.205 --> 01:57:59.582
It's over.

1329
01:59:07.107 --> 01:59:07.942
Phastos.

1330
01:59:12.363 --> 01:59:14.156
I have to try and stop this.

1331
01:59:14.323 --> 01:59:16.075
I need to get closer to Tiamut.

1332
01:59:16.242 --> 01:59:18.035
-Keep Ikaris busy.
-We've got you.

1333
01:59:18.202 --> 01:59:19.203
Go.

1334
01:59:28.045 --> 01:59:28.963
Enough.

1335
01:59:59.159 --> 02:00:00.411
Thena. stop!

1336
02:00:32.526 --> 02:00:33.903
Why are you helping Ikaris?

1337
02:00:34.778 --> 02:00:36.155
We can't let it absorb our powers.

1338
02:00:37.489 --> 02:00:38.616
Too late.

1339
02:00:40.284 --> 02:00:42.912
Thena. he's trying to goad you. Don't...

1340
02:00:58.802 --> 02:00:59.803
Makkari!

1341
02:01:08.979 --> 02:01:10.189
Where's Sersi?

1342
02:01:10.564 --> 02:01:12.733
You always did underestimate her.

1343
02:01:14.193 --> 02:01:15.444
Oh. no.

1344
02:01:16.278 --> 02:01:17.905
Not so fast.

1345
02:01:22.368 --> 02:01:23.744
Boss.

1346
02:01:27.915 --> 02:01:30.793
I don't know about you.
but this is really satisfying. right?

1347
02:01:30.960 --> 02:01:33.295
Let me go. Phastos! I can't let her do this!

1348
02:01:33.462 --> 02:01:34.755
I don't think so.

1349
02:01:35.172 --> 02:01:38.634
I've been wanting to clip your wings
for a long time. Ikaris!

1350
02:01:51.939 --> 02:01:52.940
Thena.

1351
02:01:55.651 --> 02:01:58.571
Oh. you've changed.

1352
02:01:59.947 --> 02:02:01.574
You're broken.

1353
02:02:02.408 --> 02:02:03.909
Damaged.

1354
02:02:04.493 --> 02:02:06.328
Useless.

1355
02:02:08.581 --> 02:02:12.418
You can't protect any of them.

1356
02:02:26.348 --> 02:02:27.725
Sersi.

1357
02:02:32.479 --> 02:02:35.399
You're not powerful enough to do this.

1358
02:02:35.566 --> 02:02:37.484
And you won't.

1359
02:02:37.902 --> 02:02:39.653
You're not a killer.

1360
02:02:39.820 --> 02:02:41.405
Maybe I've changed.

1361
02:02:41.864 --> 02:02:44.366
And is this really who you are. Sprite?

1362
02:02:44.533 --> 02:02:47.161
Are you really willing
to let everyone on this planet die?

1363
02:02:55.961 --> 02:02:57.755
I'm sorry. Sersi.

1364
02:03:10.226 --> 02:03:12.436
I've always envied you. Sersi.

1365
02:03:14.522 --> 02:03:16.565
'Cause you get to live as one of them.

1366
02:03:17.107 --> 02:03:18.192
And I never could.

1367
02:03:19.443 --> 02:03:21.695
You know why I hated living with humans?

1368
02:03:22.279 --> 02:03:25.074
Because they reminded me of
things I didn't even know I wanted.

1369
02:03:25.574 --> 02:03:28.953
Because of them. now I wanna know
what it feels like to grow up.

1370
02:03:30.079 --> 02:03:31.789
To fall in love.

1371
02:03:32.581 --> 02:03:34.208
To have a family.

1372
02:03:35.501 --> 02:03:39.171
And to know. in the end. I've lived.

1373
02:03:46.303 --> 02:03:47.429
It's all over now.

1374
02:03:48.264 --> 02:03:50.599
We get to start over somewhere new.

1375
02:03:54.520 --> 02:03:56.146
Well. that was very moving.

1376
02:03:56.313 --> 02:03:57.565
Druig.

1377
02:04:03.279 --> 02:04:04.822
I can't do this.

1378
02:04:08.492 --> 02:04:10.369
This is your fight now.

1379
02:04:54.955 --> 02:04:56.165
Thena.

1380
02:04:57.541 --> 02:04:58.792
It's me.

1381
02:04:59.376 --> 02:05:00.544
Gilgamesh.

1382
02:05:01.962 --> 02:05:03.005
Look at me.

1383
02:05:04.048 --> 02:05:05.341
Gilgamesh?

1384
02:05:05.508 --> 02:05:07.051
Stay here.

1385
02:05:09.762 --> 02:05:11.013
Say it.

1386
02:05:11.555 --> 02:05:13.224
Stay here.

1387
02:05:14.099 --> 02:05:15.809
You'll be okay.

1388
02:05:17.853 --> 02:05:19.688
Give me your hand.

1389
02:05:32.993 --> 02:05:34.203
It's a shame.

1390
02:05:36.247 --> 02:05:37.873
You and I...

1391
02:05:38.457 --> 02:05:40.376
we're just tools of a god.

1392
02:05:41.752 --> 02:05:44.964
Built to kill.

1393
02:05:47.800 --> 02:05:49.051
Thena.

1394
02:05:52.513 --> 02:05:53.889
Remember.

1395
02:06:24.378 --> 02:06:25.963
I remember.

1396
02:07:55.261 --> 02:07:56.720
Come on. Sersi.

1397
02:07:57.763 --> 02:07:58.848
Come on.

1398
02:10:08.018 --> 02:10:09.770
It's beautiful. isn't it?

1399
02:12:38.919 --> 02:12:40.462
I'm sorry.

1400
02:12:42.173 --> 02:12:43.632
I know.

1401
02:13:59.208 --> 02:14:00.251
How?

1402
02:14:00.709 --> 02:14:02.086
How did you do it?

1403
02:14:03.212 --> 02:14:06.465
When I touched Tiamut's palm.
I felt energy surging into me.

1404
02:14:06.882 --> 02:14:09.260
Tiamut joined our Uni-Mind.

1405
02:14:09.426 --> 02:14:10.761
I always wondered how we survived...

1406
02:14:10.928 --> 02:14:13.597
the destruction of other planets
that we were on.

1407
02:14:13.973 --> 02:14:16.475
By being connected to the Celestial
as it emerged.

1408
02:15:20.206 --> 02:15:21.415
Is he gone?

1409
02:15:31.091 --> 02:15:32.343
Sprite.

1410
02:15:34.845 --> 02:15:37.431
I still have energy from the Uni-Mind.

1411
02:15:38.390 --> 02:15:40.559
I think I can make you human.

1412
02:15:41.936 --> 02:15:44.855
All the things you said you wanted.
you can have them.

1413
02:15:45.022 --> 02:15:47.900
But your time will be fleeting
and you'll die one day.

1414
02:15:48.067 --> 02:15:49.109
Are you ready for that?

1415
02:15:51.529 --> 02:15:52.947
I am.

1416
02:16:30.359 --> 02:16:32.486
{\an8}<i>The sudden appearance of an enormous
stone figure in the Indian Ocean...</i>

1417
02:16:34.154 --> 02:16:36.949
{\an8}<i>...has left more questions than answers
for authorities.</i>

1418
02:16:37.825 --> 02:16:41.327
<i>U.S. and Australian naval ships
are maintaining defensive positions...</i>

1419
02:16:41.495 --> 02:16:42.495
<i>but at this...</i>

1420
02:16:42.663 --> 02:16:44.540
You guys did that?

1421
02:16:45.332 --> 02:16:47.626
I love you so much.

1422
02:16:54.924 --> 02:16:56.302
Are you okay?

1423
02:16:57.218 --> 02:16:59.221
I get confused sometimes.

1424
02:16:59.388 --> 02:17:01.432
Yeah. Me. too.

1425
02:17:04.018 --> 02:17:06.312
So. Dad said you're the goddess Athena.

1426
02:17:06.477 --> 02:17:08.564
"Thena." Drop the "A."

1427
02:17:11.483 --> 02:17:13.318
What's your superpower?

1428
02:17:17.198 --> 02:17:19.450
Can you just... Look... One second.

1429
02:17:20.200 --> 02:17:21.826
Okay. All right.

1430
02:17:22.369 --> 02:17:24.079
See. that thing is... Okay.

1431
02:17:24.245 --> 02:17:25.748
Almost gave you a shave and a haircut.
didn't she?

1432
02:17:25.915 --> 02:17:27.374
Stand behind me. actually.

1433
02:17:27.540 --> 02:17:29.502
You remember earmuffs?
Remember how we practiced earmuffs?

1434
02:17:29.668 --> 02:17:31.378
Thank you so much.

1435
02:17:33.547 --> 02:17:36.258
You know that your babysitting privileges
are completely revoked. right?

1436
02:17:36.424 --> 02:17:37.468
Like. it's done.

1437
02:17:37.968 --> 02:17:39.844
Thank you. Violence... Hey.

1438
02:17:40.012 --> 02:17:42.848
Violence is never the answer.
Right. T?

1439
02:17:43.014 --> 02:17:45.643
You gotta always use your brain.

1440
02:17:45.808 --> 02:17:47.520
Like you did fighting on the beach?

1441
02:17:47.686 --> 02:17:48.938
Your dad...

1442
02:17:49.103 --> 02:17:51.482
spoke calmly and firmly to the bad guy...

1443
02:17:51.648 --> 02:17:53.150
and he had no choice but to listen to me.
so no violence.

1444
02:17:57.237 --> 02:17:58.739
When are you guys leaving?
When is that happening?

1445
02:17:58.906 --> 02:18:00.782
That's happening soon. right?

1446
02:18:00.950 --> 02:18:03.786
Yes. there's Druig.
Don't go anywhere near him.

1447
02:18:04.327 --> 02:18:05.454
Yeah!

1448
02:18:07.873 --> 02:18:09.208
Okay. that's far enough. Jack.

1449
02:18:09.375 --> 02:18:11.709
Wow. Dad. the <i>Domo</i>'s so cool.

1450
02:18:11.877 --> 02:18:13.504
Your dad fixed that with his bare hands.

1451
02:18:13.671 --> 02:18:15.255
Can we go to space. too. one day?

1452
02:18:15.422 --> 02:18:17.924
Let's wait till you get
your learner's permit. okay?

1453
02:18:18.800 --> 02:18:20.218
Hey. Phastos.

1454
02:18:21.053 --> 02:18:22.429
Take care.

1455
02:18:22.805 --> 02:18:24.389
This world is lucky to have you.

1456
02:18:25.224 --> 02:18:26.851
Thank you.

1457
02:18:27.017 --> 02:18:28.686
I know you're not a hugger. so...

1458
02:18:31.856 --> 02:18:32.940
Okay.

1459
02:18:35.901 --> 02:18:39.989
You think when we find
the other Eternals out there...

1460
02:18:40.155 --> 02:18:43.157
that they'll accept the truth the way we did?

1461
02:19:01.050 --> 02:19:02.761
Told you that thing was addictive.

1462
02:19:03.929 --> 02:19:04.972
Please visit?

1463
02:19:05.598 --> 02:19:06.807
I'll try.

1464
02:19:07.391 --> 02:19:08.726
When I get time off from school.

1465
02:19:08.893 --> 02:19:11.562
Oh. wow. Listen. it's gonna be good for you
to be in a human environment.

1466
02:19:11.728 --> 02:19:13.522
You'll pick up some social skills.

1467
02:19:14.064 --> 02:19:15.441
Oh. you didn't think you needed those?

1468
02:19:16.816 --> 02:19:18.818
That explains so much.

1469
02:19:28.537 --> 02:19:30.080
Gonna miss you.

1470
02:19:30.623 --> 02:19:31.832
Me. too.

1471
02:19:35.503 --> 02:19:36.629
Madam.

1472
02:19:37.087 --> 02:19:38.379
Thanks. Karun.

1473
02:19:38.964 --> 02:19:41.424
Sometimes I wonder if we did the right thing.

1474
02:19:43.052 --> 02:19:44.136
Killing Tiamut.

1475
02:19:44.303 --> 02:19:46.055
It's too late for that.

1476
02:19:46.222 --> 02:19:48.182
But you followed your heart.

1477
02:19:48.349 --> 02:19:49.808
We all did.

1478
02:19:52.019 --> 02:19:53.020
Even Ikaris.

1479
02:20:00.611 --> 02:20:02.571
Looks like someone's waiting for you.

1480
02:20:03.739 --> 02:20:05.866
He's a lot cuter in person.

1481
02:20:08.285 --> 02:20:11.497
So. after all that.
you still can't change me into a giraffe?

1482
02:20:12.164 --> 02:20:15.835
Well. I could next time
I'm connected to a Celestial...

1483
02:20:16.001 --> 02:20:18.212
during an emergence
whilst performing a Uni-Mind.

1484
02:20:18.379 --> 02:20:21.173
Yeah. That sounds like a "no" to me.

1485
02:20:25.135 --> 02:20:26.554
What'll you do now?

1486
02:20:26.720 --> 02:20:28.013
Not sure.

1487
02:20:28.180 --> 02:20:30.182
This planet's my home. but...

1488
02:20:31.934 --> 02:20:34.645
I can't pretend to be human anymore.

1489
02:20:41.235 --> 02:20:42.820
I love you. Sersi.

1490
02:20:44.363 --> 02:20:45.447
I don't care what you are.

1491
02:20:59.253 --> 02:21:01.881
Remember when we talked about
no more secrets?

1492
02:21:02.047 --> 02:21:05.050
I have no more secrets. I promise.

1493
02:21:05.217 --> 02:21:06.719
Actually...

1494
02:21:06.886 --> 02:21:09.180
I have one I want to tell you.

1495
02:21:10.264 --> 02:21:11.807
What is it?

1496
02:21:13.767 --> 02:21:16.270
It turns out my family history is...

1497
02:21:17.188 --> 02:21:18.772
complicated.

1498
02:21:22.193 --> 02:21:23.569
Sersi?

1499
02:21:24.361 --> 02:21:25.863
Sersi. what's wrong?

1500
02:21:27.323 --> 02:21:28.657
Sersi?

1501
02:21:52.473 --> 02:21:53.849
Sersi?

1502
02:21:54.725 --> 02:21:55.976
Sersi?

1503
02:21:56.852 --> 02:21:59.021
Sersi!

1504
02:22:13.827 --> 02:22:17.206
You have chosen to sacrifice a Celestial...

1505
02:22:17.581 --> 02:22:20.000
for the people of this planet.

1506
02:22:21.293 --> 02:22:23.087
I will spare them...

1507
02:22:23.254 --> 02:22:27.967
but your memories will show
if they're worthy to live.

1508
02:22:29.468 --> 02:22:33.681
And I will return for judgment.

1509
02:22:49.071 --> 02:22:51.115
You all right. Ted?

1510
02:22:52.825 --> 02:22:54.702
Did you see that?

1511
02:26:04.308 --> 02:26:05.643
Arishem.

1512
02:26:07.895 --> 02:26:09.605
We have to go back.

1513
02:26:22.576 --> 02:26:23.911
What?

1514
02:26:36.799 --> 02:26:37.883
Wow.

1515
02:26:38.759 --> 02:26:41.387
My ears. My eyes are numb.

1516
02:26:41.554 --> 02:26:44.390
No more drunk teleporting for you.

1517
02:26:45.724 --> 02:26:46.892
Hang on. hang on.

1518
02:26:52.773 --> 02:26:54.233
Behold...

1519
02:26:54.900 --> 02:26:57.486
the royal prince of Titan...

1520
02:26:57.653 --> 02:27:00.865
brother of Thanos. the Knave of Hearts...

1521
02:27:01.031 --> 02:27:02.116
defeater...

1522
02:27:03.450 --> 02:27:05.411
-...of Black Robert...
-Roger.

1523
02:27:07.329 --> 02:27:09.790
Defeater of Black Roger.

1524
02:27:10.416 --> 02:27:11.709
The great adventurer...

1525
02:27:12.251 --> 02:27:16.172
Starfox of Mystery Planet.

1526
02:27:16.755 --> 02:27:18.966
What a pleasure to make your acquaintance...

1527
02:27:19.508 --> 02:27:21.385
my fellow Eternals.

1528
02:27:22.428 --> 02:27:24.763
You know. you really don't have to
do the whole thing every time.

1529
02:27:24.930 --> 02:27:26.140
Everything you do is impressive.

1530
02:27:26.307 --> 02:27:27.308
-What am I gonna leave off the list?
-No. I know it's impressive.

1531
02:27:27.558 --> 02:27:28.559
Who are you?

1532
02:27:30.811 --> 02:27:31.937
I'm Eros.

1533
02:27:32.438 --> 02:27:33.480
This is Pip.

1534
02:27:33.898 --> 02:27:37.109
And you are as beautiful
as legends say. Thena.

1535
02:27:37.276 --> 02:27:38.569
What do you want. lads?

1536
02:27:38.736 --> 02:27:40.404
Pip and I are here to help.
aren't we?

1537
02:27:45.868 --> 02:27:47.953
Your friends are in big trouble.

1538
02:27:49.622 --> 02:27:51.707
And we know where to find them.

1539
02:34:43.118 --> 02:34:44.578
You can do this.

1540
02:34:45.829 --> 02:34:47.665
You can do this.

1541
02:35:11.939 --> 02:35:13.440
I'm sorry.

1542
02:35:15.651 --> 02:35:17.278
I have to try.

1543
02:35:31.375 --> 02:35:33.961
Sure you're ready for that. Mr. Whitman?

1544
02:35:40.089 --> 02:35:45.089
